114 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Pointer )
115 ft_service_list_lookup( FT_ServiceDesc service_descriptors,
116 const char* service_id )
117 {
118 FT_Pointer result = NULL;
119 FT_ServiceDesc desc = service_descriptors;
120
121
122 if ( desc && service_id )
123 {
124 for ( ; desc->serv_id != NULL; desc++ )
125 {
126 if ( ft_strcmp( desc->serv_id, service_id ) == 0 )
127 {
128 result = (FT_Pointer)desc->serv_data;
129 break;
130 }
131 }
132 }
133
134 return result;
135 }

161 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
162 ft_validator_error( FT_Validator valid,
163 FT_Error error )
164 {
165 /* since the cast below also disables the compiler's */
166 /* type check, we introduce a dummy variable, which */
167 /* will be optimized away */
168 volatile ft_jmp_buf* jump_buffer = &valid->jump_buffer;
169
170
171 valid->error = error;
172
173 /* throw away volatileness; use `jump_buffer' or the */
174 /* compiler may warn about an unused local variable */
175 ft_longjmp( *(ft_jmp_buf*) jump_buffer, 1 );
176 }

192 /* create a new input stream from an FT_Open_Args structure */
193 /* */
194 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
195 FT_Stream_New( FT_Library library,
196 const FT_Open_Args* args,
197 FT_Stream *astream )
198 {
199 FT_Error error;
200 FT_Memory memory;
201 FT_Stream stream = NULL;
202 FT_UInt mode;
203
204
205 *astream = NULL;
206
207 if ( !library )
208 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Library_Handle );
209
210 if ( !args )
211 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
212
213 memory = library->memory;
214 mode = args->flags &
215 ( FT_OPEN_MEMORY | FT_OPEN_STREAM | FT_OPEN_PATHNAME );
216
217 if ( mode == FT_OPEN_MEMORY )
218 {
219 /* create a memory-based stream */
220 if ( FT_NEW( stream ) )
221 goto Exit;
222
223 FT_Stream_OpenMemory( stream,
224 (const FT_Byte*)args->memory_base,
225 (FT_ULong)args->memory_size );
226 stream->memory = memory;
227 }
228
229#ifndef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_DISABLE_STREAM_SUPPORT
230
231 else if ( mode == FT_OPEN_PATHNAME )
232 {
233 /* create a normal system stream */
234 if ( FT_NEW( stream ) )
235 goto Exit;
236
237 stream->memory = memory;
238 error = FT_Stream_Open( stream, args->pathname );
239 if ( error )
240 FT_FREE( stream );
241 }
242 else if ( ( mode == FT_OPEN_STREAM ) && args->stream )
243 {
244 /* use an existing, user-provided stream */
245
246 /* in this case, we do not need to allocate a new stream object */
247 /* since the caller is responsible for closing it himself */
248 stream = args->stream;
249 stream->memory = memory;
250 error = FT_Err_Ok;
251 }
252
253#endif
254
255 else
256 {
257 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
258 if ( ( args->flags & FT_OPEN_STREAM ) && args->stream )
259 FT_Stream_Close( args->stream );
260 }
261
262 if ( !error )
263 *astream = stream;
264
265 Exit:
266 return error;
267 }
268
269
270 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
271 FT_Stream_Free( FT_Stream stream,
272 FT_Int external )
273 {
274 if ( stream )
275 {
276 FT_Memory memory = stream->memory;
277
278
279 FT_Stream_Close( stream );
280
281 if ( !external )
282 FT_FREE( stream );
283 }
284 }

310 static FT_Error
311 ft_glyphslot_init( FT_GlyphSlot slot )
312 {
313 FT_Driver driver = slot->face->driver;
314 FT_Driver_Class clazz = driver->clazz;
315 FT_Memory memory = driver->root.memory;
316 FT_Error error = FT_Err_Ok;
317 FT_Slot_Internal internal = NULL;
318
319
320 slot->library = driver->root.library;
321
322 if ( FT_NEW( internal ) )
323 goto Exit;
324
325 slot->internal = internal;
326
327 if ( FT_DRIVER_USES_OUTLINES( driver ) )
328 error = FT_GlyphLoader_New( memory, &internal->loader );
329
330 if ( !error && clazz->init_slot )
331 error = clazz->init_slot( slot );
332
333#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SVG
334 /* if SVG table exists, allocate the space in `slot->other` */
335 if ( slot->face->face_flags & FT_FACE_FLAG_SVG )
336 {
337 FT_SVG_Document document = NULL;
338
339
340 if ( FT_NEW( document ) )
341 goto Exit;
342 slot->other = document;
343 }
344#endif
345
346 Exit:
347 return error;
348 }

351 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
352 ft_glyphslot_free_bitmap( FT_GlyphSlot slot )
353 {
354 if ( slot->internal && ( slot->internal->flags & FT_GLYPH_OWN_BITMAP ) )
355 {
356 FT_Memory memory = FT_FACE_MEMORY( slot->face );
357
358
359 FT_FREE( slot->bitmap.buffer );
360 slot->internal->flags &= ~FT_GLYPH_OWN_BITMAP;
361 }
362 else
363 {
364 /* assume that the bitmap buffer was stolen or not */
365 /* allocated from the heap */
366 slot->bitmap.buffer = NULL;
367 }
368 }

370
371 /* overflow-resistant presetting of bitmap position and dimensions; */
372 /* also check whether the size is too large for rendering */
373 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Bool )
374 ft_glyphslot_preset_bitmap( FT_GlyphSlot slot,
375 FT_Render_Mode mode,
376 const FT_Vector* origin )
377 {
378 FT_Outline* outline = &slot->outline;
379 FT_Bitmap* bitmap = &slot->bitmap;
380
381 FT_Pixel_Mode pixel_mode;
382
383 FT_BBox cbox, pbox;
384 FT_Pos x_shift = 0;
385 FT_Pos y_shift = 0;
386 FT_Pos x_left, y_top;
387 FT_Pos width, height, pitch;
388
389
390 if ( slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_SVG )
391 {
392 FT_Module module;
393 SVG_Service svg_service;
394
395
396 module = FT_Get_Module( slot->library, "ot-svg" );
397 svg_service = (SVG_Service)module->clazz->module_interface;
398
399 return (FT_Bool)svg_service->preset_slot( module, slot, FALSE );
400 }
401 else if ( slot->format != FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE )
402 return 1;
403
404 if ( origin )
405 {
406 x_shift = origin->x;
407 y_shift = origin->y;
408 }
409
410 /* compute the control box, and grid-fit it, */
411 /* taking into account the origin shift */
412 FT_Outline_Get_CBox( outline, &cbox );
413
414 /* rough estimate of pixel box */
415 pbox.xMin = ( cbox.xMin >> 6 ) + ( x_shift >> 6 );
416 pbox.yMin = ( cbox.yMin >> 6 ) + ( y_shift >> 6 );
417 pbox.xMax = ( cbox.xMax >> 6 ) + ( x_shift >> 6 );
418 pbox.yMax = ( cbox.yMax >> 6 ) + ( y_shift >> 6 );
419
420 /* tiny remainder box */
421 cbox.xMin = ( cbox.xMin & 63 ) + ( x_shift & 63 );
422 cbox.yMin = ( cbox.yMin & 63 ) + ( y_shift & 63 );
423 cbox.xMax = ( cbox.xMax & 63 ) + ( x_shift & 63 );
424 cbox.yMax = ( cbox.yMax & 63 ) + ( y_shift & 63 );
425
426 switch ( mode )
427 {
428 case FT_RENDER_MODE_MONO:
429 pixel_mode = FT_PIXEL_MODE_MONO;
430#if 1
431 /* x */
432
433 /* undocumented but confirmed: bbox values get rounded; */
434 /* we do asymmetric rounding so that the center of a pixel */
435 /* gets always included */
436
437 pbox.xMin += ( cbox.xMin + 31 ) >> 6;
438 pbox.xMax += ( cbox.xMax + 32 ) >> 6;
439
440 /* if the bbox collapsed, we add a pixel based on the total */
441 /* rounding remainder to cover most of the original cbox */
442
443 if ( pbox.xMin == pbox.xMax )
444 {
445 if ( ( ( cbox.xMin + 31 ) & 63 ) - 31 +
446 ( ( cbox.xMax + 32 ) & 63 ) - 32 < 0 )
447 pbox.xMin -= 1;
448 else
449 pbox.xMax += 1;
450 }
451
452 /* y */
453
454 pbox.yMin += ( cbox.yMin + 31 ) >> 6;
455 pbox.yMax += ( cbox.yMax + 32 ) >> 6;
456
457 if ( pbox.yMin == pbox.yMax )
458 {
459 if ( ( ( cbox.yMin + 31 ) & 63 ) - 31 +
460 ( ( cbox.yMax + 32 ) & 63 ) - 32 < 0 )
461 pbox.yMin -= 1;
462 else
463 pbox.yMax += 1;
464 }
465
466 break;
467#else
468 goto Adjust;
469#endif
470
471 case FT_RENDER_MODE_LCD:
472 pixel_mode = FT_PIXEL_MODE_LCD;
473 ft_lcd_padding( &cbox, slot, mode );
474 goto Adjust;
475
476 case FT_RENDER_MODE_LCD_V:
477 pixel_mode = FT_PIXEL_MODE_LCD_V;
478 ft_lcd_padding( &cbox, slot, mode );
479 goto Adjust;
480
481 case FT_RENDER_MODE_NORMAL:
482 case FT_RENDER_MODE_LIGHT:
483 default:
484 pixel_mode = FT_PIXEL_MODE_GRAY;
485 Adjust:
486 pbox.xMin += cbox.xMin >> 6;
487 pbox.yMin += cbox.yMin >> 6;
488 pbox.xMax += ( cbox.xMax + 63 ) >> 6;
489 pbox.yMax += ( cbox.yMax + 63 ) >> 6;
490 }
491
492 x_left = pbox.xMin;
493 y_top = pbox.yMax;
494
495 width = pbox.xMax - pbox.xMin;
496 height = pbox.yMax - pbox.yMin;
497
498 switch ( pixel_mode )
499 {
500 case FT_PIXEL_MODE_MONO:
501 pitch = ( ( width + 15 ) >> 4 ) << 1;
502 break;
503
504 case FT_PIXEL_MODE_LCD:
505 width *= 3;
506 pitch = FT_PAD_CEIL( width, 4 );
507 break;
508
509 case FT_PIXEL_MODE_LCD_V:
510 height *= 3;
511 FALL_THROUGH;
512
513 case FT_PIXEL_MODE_GRAY:
514 default:
515 pitch = width;
516 }
517
518 slot->bitmap_left = (FT_Int)x_left;
519 slot->bitmap_top = (FT_Int)y_top;
520
521 bitmap->pixel_mode = (unsigned char)pixel_mode;
522 bitmap->num_grays = 256;
523 bitmap->width = (unsigned int)width;
524 bitmap->rows = (unsigned int)height;
525 bitmap->pitch = pitch;
526
527 if ( pbox.xMin < -0x8000 || pbox.xMax > 0x7FFF ||
528 pbox.yMin < -0x8000 || pbox.yMax > 0x7FFF )
529 {
530 FT_TRACE3(( "ft_glyphslot_preset_bitmap: [%ld %ld %ld %ld]\n",
531 pbox.xMin, pbox.yMin, pbox.xMax, pbox.yMax ));
532 return 1;
533 }
534
535 return 0;
536 }

539 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
540 ft_glyphslot_set_bitmap( FT_GlyphSlot slot,
541 FT_Byte* buffer )
542 {
543 ft_glyphslot_free_bitmap( slot );
544
545 slot->bitmap.buffer = buffer;
546
547 FT_ASSERT( (slot->internal->flags & FT_GLYPH_OWN_BITMAP) == 0 );
548 }

551 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
552 ft_glyphslot_alloc_bitmap( FT_GlyphSlot slot,
553 FT_ULong size )
554 {
555 FT_Memory memory = FT_FACE_MEMORY( slot->face );
556 FT_Error error;
557
558
559 if ( slot->internal->flags & FT_GLYPH_OWN_BITMAP )
560 FT_FREE( slot->bitmap.buffer );
561 else
562 slot->internal->flags |= FT_GLYPH_OWN_BITMAP;
563
564 FT_MEM_ALLOC( slot->bitmap.buffer, size );
565 return error;
566 }

569 static void
570 ft_glyphslot_clear( FT_GlyphSlot slot )
571 {
572 /* free bitmap if needed */
573 ft_glyphslot_free_bitmap( slot );
574
575 /* clear all public fields in the glyph slot */
576 slot->glyph_index = 0;
577
578 FT_ZERO( &slot->metrics );
579 FT_ZERO( &slot->outline );
580
581 slot->bitmap.width = 0;
582 slot->bitmap.rows = 0;
583 slot->bitmap.pitch = 0;
584 slot->bitmap.pixel_mode = 0;
585 /* `slot->bitmap.buffer' has been handled by ft_glyphslot_free_bitmap */
586
587 slot->bitmap_left = 0;
588 slot->bitmap_top = 0;
589 slot->num_subglyphs = 0;
590 slot->subglyphs = NULL;
591 slot->control_data = NULL;
592 slot->control_len = 0;
593
594#ifndef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SVG
595 slot->other = NULL;
596#else
597 if ( !( slot->face->face_flags & FT_FACE_FLAG_SVG ) )
598 slot->other = NULL;
599 else
600 {
601 if ( slot->internal->flags & FT_GLYPH_OWN_GZIP_SVG )
602 {
603 FT_Memory memory = slot->face->memory;
604 FT_SVG_Document doc = (FT_SVG_Document)slot->other;
605
606
607 FT_FREE( doc->svg_document );
608 slot->internal->flags &= ~FT_GLYPH_OWN_GZIP_SVG;
609 }
610 }
611#endif
612
613 slot->format = FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_NONE;
614
615 slot->linearHoriAdvance = 0;
616 slot->linearVertAdvance = 0;
617 slot->advance.x = 0;
618 slot->advance.y = 0;
619 slot->lsb_delta = 0;
620 slot->rsb_delta = 0;
621 }

623
624 static void
625 ft_glyphslot_done( FT_GlyphSlot slot )
626 {
627 FT_Driver driver = slot->face->driver;
628 FT_Driver_Class clazz = driver->clazz;
629 FT_Memory memory = driver->root.memory;
630
631#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SVG
632 if ( slot->face->face_flags & FT_FACE_FLAG_SVG )
633 {
634 /* Free memory in case SVG was there. */
635 /* `slot->internal` might be NULL in out-of-memory situations. */
636 if ( slot->internal && slot->internal->flags & FT_GLYPH_OWN_GZIP_SVG )
637 {
638 FT_SVG_Document doc = (FT_SVG_Document)slot->other;
639
640
641 FT_FREE( doc->svg_document );
642
643 slot->internal->flags &= ~FT_GLYPH_OWN_GZIP_SVG;
644 }
645
646 FT_FREE( slot->other );
647 }
648#endif
649
650 if ( clazz->done_slot )
651 clazz->done_slot( slot );
652
653 /* free bitmap buffer if needed */
654 ft_glyphslot_free_bitmap( slot );
655
656 /* slot->internal might be NULL in out-of-memory situations */
657 if ( slot->internal )
658 {
659 /* free glyph loader */
660 if ( FT_DRIVER_USES_OUTLINES( driver ) )
661 {
662 FT_GlyphLoader_Done( slot->internal->loader );
663 slot->internal->loader = NULL;
664 }
665
666 FT_FREE( slot->internal );
667 }
668 }

671 /* documentation is in ftobjs.h */
672
673 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
674 FT_New_GlyphSlot( FT_Face face,
675 FT_GlyphSlot *aslot )
676 {
677 FT_Error error;
678 FT_Driver driver;
679 FT_Driver_Class clazz;
680 FT_Memory memory;
681 FT_GlyphSlot slot = NULL;
682
683
684 if ( !face )
685 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Face_Handle );
686
687 if ( !face->driver )
688 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
689
690 driver = face->driver;
691 clazz = driver->clazz;
692 memory = driver->root.memory;
693
694 FT_TRACE4(( "FT_New_GlyphSlot: Creating new slot object\n" ));
695 if ( !FT_ALLOC( slot, clazz->slot_object_size ) )
696 {
697 slot->face = face;
698
699 error = ft_glyphslot_init( slot );
700 if ( error )
701 {
702 ft_glyphslot_done( slot );
703 FT_FREE( slot );
704 goto Exit;
705 }
706
707 slot->next = face->glyph;
708 face->glyph = slot;
709
710 if ( aslot )
711 *aslot = slot;
712 }
713 else if ( aslot )
714 *aslot = NULL;
715
716
717 Exit:
718 FT_TRACE4(( "FT_New_GlyphSlot: Return 0x%x\n", error ));
719
720 return error;
721 }

724 /* documentation is in ftobjs.h */
725
726 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
727 FT_Done_GlyphSlot( FT_GlyphSlot slot )
728 {
729 if ( slot )
730 {
731 FT_Driver driver = slot->face->driver;
732 FT_Memory memory = driver->root.memory;
733 FT_GlyphSlot prev;
734 FT_GlyphSlot cur;
735
736
737 /* Remove slot from its parent face's list */
738 prev = NULL;
739 cur = slot->face->glyph;
740
741 while ( cur )
742 {
743 if ( cur == slot )
744 {
745 if ( !prev )
746 slot->face->glyph = cur->next;
747 else
748 prev->next = cur->next;
749
750 /* finalize client-specific data */
751 if ( slot->generic.finalizer )
752 slot->generic.finalizer( slot );
753
754 ft_glyphslot_done( slot );
755 FT_FREE( slot );
756 break;
757 }
758 prev = cur;
759 cur = cur->next;
760 }
761 }
762 }

765 /* documentation is in freetype.h */
766
767 FT_EXPORT_DEF( void )
768 FT_Set_Transform( FT_Face face,
769 FT_Matrix* matrix,
770 FT_Vector* delta )
771 {
772 FT_Face_Internal internal;
773
774
775 if ( !face )
776 return;
777
778 internal = face->internal;
779
780 internal->transform_flags = 0;
781
782 if ( !matrix )
783 {
784 internal->transform_matrix.xx = 0x10000L;
785 internal->transform_matrix.xy = 0;
786 internal->transform_matrix.yx = 0;
787 internal->transform_matrix.yy = 0x10000L;
788
789 matrix = &internal->transform_matrix;
790 }
791 else
792 internal->transform_matrix = *matrix;
793
794 /* set transform_flags bit flag 0 if `matrix' isn't the identity */
795 if ( ( matrix->xy | matrix->yx ) ||
796 matrix->xx != 0x10000L ||
797 matrix->yy != 0x10000L )
798 internal->transform_flags |= 1;
799
800 if ( !delta )
801 {
802 internal->transform_delta.x = 0;
803 internal->transform_delta.y = 0;
804
805 delta = &internal->transform_delta;
806 }
807 else
808 internal->transform_delta = *delta;
809
810 /* set transform_flags bit flag 1 if `delta' isn't the null vector */
811 if ( delta->x | delta->y )
812 internal->transform_flags |= 2;
813 }

818 FT_EXPORT_DEF( void )
819 FT_Get_Transform( FT_Face face,
820 FT_Matrix* matrix,
821 FT_Vector* delta )
822 {
823 FT_Face_Internal internal;
824
825
826 if ( !face )
827 return;
828
829 internal = face->internal;
830
831 if ( matrix )
832 *matrix = internal->transform_matrix;
833
834 if ( delta )
835 *delta = internal->transform_delta;
836 }

844 static void
845 ft_glyphslot_grid_fit_metrics( FT_GlyphSlot slot,
846 FT_Bool vertical )
847 {
848 FT_Glyph_Metrics* metrics = &slot->metrics;
849 FT_Pos right, bottom;
850
851
852 if ( vertical )
853 {
854 metrics->horiBearingX = FT_PIX_FLOOR( metrics->horiBearingX );
855 metrics->horiBearingY = FT_PIX_CEIL_LONG( metrics->horiBearingY );
856
857 right = FT_PIX_CEIL_LONG( ADD_LONG( metrics->vertBearingX,
858 metrics->width ) );
859 bottom = FT_PIX_CEIL_LONG( ADD_LONG( metrics->vertBearingY,
860 metrics->height ) );
861
862 metrics->vertBearingX = FT_PIX_FLOOR( metrics->vertBearingX );
863 metrics->vertBearingY = FT_PIX_FLOOR( metrics->vertBearingY );
864
865 metrics->width = SUB_LONG( right,
866 metrics->vertBearingX );
867 metrics->height = SUB_LONG( bottom,
868 metrics->vertBearingY );
869 }
870 else
871 {
872 metrics->vertBearingX = FT_PIX_FLOOR( metrics->vertBearingX );
873 metrics->vertBearingY = FT_PIX_FLOOR( metrics->vertBearingY );
874
875 right = FT_PIX_CEIL_LONG( ADD_LONG( metrics->horiBearingX,
876 metrics->width ) );
877 bottom = FT_PIX_FLOOR( SUB_LONG( metrics->horiBearingY,
878 metrics->height ) );
879
880 metrics->horiBearingX = FT_PIX_FLOOR( metrics->horiBearingX );
881 metrics->horiBearingY = FT_PIX_CEIL_LONG( metrics->horiBearingY );
882
883 metrics->width = SUB_LONG( right,
884 metrics->horiBearingX );
885 metrics->height = SUB_LONG( metrics->horiBearingY,
886 bottom );
887 }
888
889 metrics->horiAdvance = FT_PIX_ROUND_LONG( metrics->horiAdvance );
890 metrics->vertAdvance = FT_PIX_ROUND_LONG( metrics->vertAdvance );
891 }
892#endif /* GRID_FIT_METRICS */

895 /* documentation is in freetype.h */
896
897 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
898 FT_Load_Glyph( FT_Face face,
899 FT_UInt glyph_index,
900 FT_Int32 load_flags )
901 {
902 FT_Error error;
903 FT_Driver driver;
904 FT_GlyphSlot slot;
905 FT_Library library;
906 FT_Bool autohint = FALSE;
907 FT_Module hinter;
908 TT_Face ttface = (TT_Face)face;
909
910
911 if ( !face || !face->size || !face->glyph )
912 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Face_Handle );
913
914 /* The validity test for `glyph_index' is performed by the */
915 /* font drivers. */
916
917 slot = face->glyph;
918 ft_glyphslot_clear( slot );
919
920 driver = face->driver;
921 library = driver->root.library;
922 hinter = library->auto_hinter;
923
924 /* undefined scale means no scale */
925 if ( face->size->metrics.x_ppem == 0 ||
926 face->size->metrics.y_ppem == 0 )
927 load_flags |= FT_LOAD_NO_SCALE;
928
929 /* resolve load flags dependencies */
930
931 if ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_RECURSE )
932 load_flags |= FT_LOAD_NO_SCALE |
933 FT_LOAD_IGNORE_TRANSFORM;
934
935 if ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_SCALE )
936 {
937 load_flags |= FT_LOAD_NO_HINTING |
938 FT_LOAD_NO_BITMAP;
939
940 load_flags &= ~FT_LOAD_RENDER;
941 }
942
943 if ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_BITMAP_METRICS_ONLY )
944 load_flags &= ~FT_LOAD_RENDER;
945
946 /*
947 * Determine whether we need to auto-hint or not.
948 * The general rules are:
949 *
950 * - Do only auto-hinting if we have
951 *
952 * - a hinter module,
953 * - a scalable font,
954 * - not a tricky font, and
955 * - no transforms except simple slants and/or rotations by
956 * integer multiples of 90 degrees.
957 *
958 * - Then, auto-hint if FT_LOAD_FORCE_AUTOHINT is set or if we don't
959 * have a native font hinter.
960 *
961 * - Otherwise, auto-hint for LIGHT hinting mode or if there isn't
962 * any hinting bytecode in the TrueType/OpenType font.
963 *
964 * - Exception: The font is `tricky' and requires the native hinter to
965 * load properly.
966 */
967
968 if ( hinter &&
969 !( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_HINTING ) &&
970 !( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_AUTOHINT ) &&
971 FT_IS_SCALABLE( face ) &&
972 !FT_IS_TRICKY( face ) &&
973 ( ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_IGNORE_TRANSFORM ) ||
974 ( face->internal->transform_matrix.yx == 0 &&
975 face->internal->transform_matrix.xx != 0 ) ||
976 ( face->internal->transform_matrix.xx == 0 &&
977 face->internal->transform_matrix.yx != 0 ) ) )
978 {
979 if ( ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_FORCE_AUTOHINT ) ||
980 !FT_DRIVER_HAS_HINTER( driver ) )
981 autohint = TRUE;
982 else
983 {
984 FT_Render_Mode mode = FT_LOAD_TARGET_MODE( load_flags );
985 FT_Bool is_light_type1;
986
987
988 /* only the new Adobe engine (for both CFF and Type 1) is `light'; */
989 /* we use `strstr' to catch both `Type 1' and `CID Type 1' */
990 is_light_type1 =
991 ft_strstr( FT_Get_Font_Format( face ), "Type 1" ) != NULL &&
992 ((PS_Driver)driver)->hinting_engine == FT_HINTING_ADOBE;
993
994 /* the check for `num_locations' assures that we actually */
995 /* test for instructions in a TTF and not in a CFF-based OTF */
996 /* */
997 /* since `maxSizeOfInstructions' might be unreliable, we */
998 /* check the size of the `fpgm' and `prep' tables, too -- */
999 /* the assumption is that there don't exist real TTFs where */
1000 /* both `fpgm' and `prep' tables are missing */
1001 if ( ( mode == FT_RENDER_MODE_LIGHT &&
1002 ( !FT_DRIVER_HINTS_LIGHTLY( driver ) &&
1003 !is_light_type1 ) ) ||
1004 ( FT_IS_SFNT( face ) &&
1005 ttface->num_locations &&
1006 ttface->max_profile.maxSizeOfInstructions == 0 &&
1007 ttface->font_program_size == 0 &&
1008 ttface->cvt_program_size == 0 ) )
1009 autohint = TRUE;
1010 }
1011 }
1012
1013 if ( autohint )
1014 {
1015 FT_AutoHinter_Interface hinting;
1016
1017
1018 /* XXX: The use of the `FT_LOAD_XXX_ONLY` flags is not very */
1019 /* elegant. */
1020
1021 /* try to load SVG documents if available */
1022 if ( ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_SVG ) == 0 &&
1023 FT_HAS_SVG( face ) )
1024 {
1025 error = driver->clazz->load_glyph( slot, face->size,
1026 glyph_index,
1027 load_flags | FT_LOAD_SVG_ONLY );
1028
1029 if ( !error && slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_SVG )
1030 goto Load_Ok;
1031 }
1032
1033 /* try to load embedded bitmaps if available */
1034 if ( FT_HAS_FIXED_SIZES( face ) &&
1035 ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_BITMAP ) == 0 )
1036 {
1037 error = driver->clazz->load_glyph( slot, face->size,
1038 glyph_index,
1039 load_flags | FT_LOAD_SBITS_ONLY );
1040
1041 if ( !error && slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_BITMAP )
1042 goto Load_Ok;
1043 }
1044
1045 {
1046 FT_Face_Internal internal = face->internal;
1047 FT_Int transform_flags = internal->transform_flags;
1048
1049
1050 /* since the auto-hinter calls FT_Load_Glyph by itself, */
1051 /* make sure that glyphs aren't transformed */
1052 internal->transform_flags = 0;
1053
1054 /* load auto-hinted outline */
1055 hinting = (FT_AutoHinter_Interface)hinter->clazz->module_interface;
1056
1057 error = hinting->load_glyph( (FT_AutoHinter)hinter,
1058 slot, face->size,
1059 glyph_index, load_flags );
1060
1061 internal->transform_flags = transform_flags;
1062 }
1063 }
1064 else
1065 {
1066 error = driver->clazz->load_glyph( slot,
1067 face->size,
1068 glyph_index,
1069 load_flags );
1070 if ( error )
1071 goto Exit;
1072
1073 if ( slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE )
1074 {
1075 /* check that the loaded outline is correct */
1076 error = FT_Outline_Check( &slot->outline );
1077 if ( error )
1078 goto Exit;
1079
1080#ifdef GRID_FIT_METRICS
1081 if ( !( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_HINTING ) )
1082 ft_glyphslot_grid_fit_metrics(
1083 slot,
1084 FT_BOOL( load_flags & FT_LOAD_VERTICAL_LAYOUT ) );
1085#endif
1086 }
1087 }
1088
1089 Load_Ok:
1090 /* compute the advance */
1091 if ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_VERTICAL_LAYOUT )
1092 {
1093 slot->advance.x = 0;
1094 slot->advance.y = slot->metrics.vertAdvance;
1095 }
1096 else
1097 {
1098 slot->advance.x = slot->metrics.horiAdvance;
1099 slot->advance.y = 0;
1100 }
1101
1102 /* compute the linear advance in 16.16 pixels */
1103 if ( ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_LINEAR_DESIGN ) == 0 &&
1104 FT_IS_SCALABLE( face ) )
1105 {
1106 FT_Size_Metrics* metrics = &face->size->metrics;
1107
1108
1109 /* it's tricky! */
1110 slot->linearHoriAdvance = FT_MulDiv( slot->linearHoriAdvance,
1111 metrics->x_scale, 64 );
1112
1113 slot->linearVertAdvance = FT_MulDiv( slot->linearVertAdvance,
1114 metrics->y_scale, 64 );
1115 }
1116
1117 if ( ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_IGNORE_TRANSFORM ) == 0 )
1118 {
1119 FT_Face_Internal internal = face->internal;
1120
1121
1122 /* now, transform the glyph image if needed */
1123 if ( internal->transform_flags )
1124 {
1125 /* get renderer */
1126 FT_Renderer renderer = ft_lookup_glyph_renderer( slot );
1127
1128
1129 if ( renderer )
1130 error = renderer->clazz->transform_glyph(
1131 renderer, slot,
1132 &internal->transform_matrix,
1133 &internal->transform_delta );
1134 else if ( slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE )
1135 {
1136 /* apply `standard' transformation if no renderer is available */
1137 if ( internal->transform_flags & 1 )
1138 FT_Outline_Transform( &slot->outline,
1139 &internal->transform_matrix );
1140
1141 if ( internal->transform_flags & 2 )
1142 FT_Outline_Translate( &slot->outline,
1143 internal->transform_delta.x,
1144 internal->transform_delta.y );
1145 }
1146
1147 /* transform advance */
1148 FT_Vector_Transform( &slot->advance, &internal->transform_matrix );
1149 }
1150 }
1151
1152 slot->glyph_index = glyph_index;
1153 slot->internal->load_flags = load_flags;
1154
1155 /* do we need to render the image or preset the bitmap now? */
1156 if ( !error &&
1157 ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_NO_SCALE ) == 0 &&
1158 slot->format != FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_BITMAP &&
1159 slot->format != FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_COMPOSITE )
1160 {
1161 FT_Render_Mode mode = FT_LOAD_TARGET_MODE( load_flags );
1162
1163
1164 if ( mode == FT_RENDER_MODE_NORMAL &&
1165 load_flags & FT_LOAD_MONOCHROME )
1166 mode = FT_RENDER_MODE_MONO;
1167
1168 if ( load_flags & FT_LOAD_RENDER )
1169 error = FT_Render_Glyph( slot, mode );
1170 else
1171 ft_glyphslot_preset_bitmap( slot, mode, NULL );
1172 }
1173
1174#ifdef FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_TRACE
1175 FT_TRACE5(( "FT_Load_Glyph: index %d, flags 0x%x\n",
1176 glyph_index, load_flags ));
1177 FT_TRACE5(( " bitmap %dx%d %s, %s (mode %d)\n",
1178 slot->bitmap.width,
1179 slot->bitmap.rows,
1180 slot->outline.points ?
1181 slot->bitmap.buffer ? "rendered"
1182 : "preset"
1183 :
1184 slot->internal->flags & FT_GLYPH_OWN_BITMAP ? "owned"
1185 : "unowned",
1186 pixel_modes[slot->bitmap.pixel_mode],
1187 slot->bitmap.pixel_mode ));
1188 FT_TRACE5(( "\n" ));
1189 FT_TRACE5(( " x advance: %f\n", (double)slot->advance.x / 64 ));
1190 FT_TRACE5(( " y advance: %f\n", (double)slot->advance.y / 64 ));
1191 FT_TRACE5(( " linear x advance: %f\n",
1192 (double)slot->linearHoriAdvance / 65536 ));
1193 FT_TRACE5(( " linear y advance: %f\n",
1194 (double)slot->linearVertAdvance / 65536 ));
1195
1196 {
1197 FT_Glyph_Metrics* metrics = &slot->metrics;
1198
1199
1200 FT_TRACE5(( " metrics:\n" ));
1201 FT_TRACE5(( " width: %f\n", (double)metrics->width / 64 ));
1202 FT_TRACE5(( " height: %f\n", (double)metrics->height / 64 ));
1203 FT_TRACE5(( "\n" ));
1204 FT_TRACE5(( " horiBearingX: %f\n",
1205 (double)metrics->horiBearingX / 64 ));
1206 FT_TRACE5(( " horiBearingY: %f\n",
1207 (double)metrics->horiBearingY / 64 ));
1208 FT_TRACE5(( " horiAdvance: %f\n",
1209 (double)metrics->horiAdvance / 64 ));
1210 FT_TRACE5(( "\n" ));
1211 FT_TRACE5(( " vertBearingX: %f\n",
1212 (double)metrics->vertBearingX / 64 ));
1213 FT_TRACE5(( " vertBearingY: %f\n",
1214 (double)metrics->vertBearingY / 64 ));
1215 FT_TRACE5(( " vertAdvance: %f\n",
1216 (double)metrics->vertAdvance / 64 ));
1217 }
1218#endif
1219
1220 Exit:
1221 return error;
1222 }

1273 static void
1274 destroy_charmaps( FT_Face face,
1275 FT_Memory memory )
1276 {

1278
1279
1280 if ( !face )
1281 return;
1282
1283 for ( n = 0; n < face->num_charmaps; n++ )
1284 {

1286

1288 ft_cmap_done_internal( cmap );
1289

1291 }
1292
1293 FT_FREE( face->charmaps );
1294 face->num_charmaps = 0;
1295 }

1298 /* destructor for faces list */
1299 static void
1300 destroy_face( FT_Memory memory,
1301 void* face_,
1302 void* driver_ )
1303 {
1304 FT_Face face = (FT_Face)face_;
1305 FT_Driver driver = (FT_Driver)driver_;
1306 FT_Driver_Class clazz = driver->clazz;
1307
1308
1309 /* discard auto-hinting data */
1310 if ( face->autohint.finalizer )
1311 face->autohint.finalizer( face->autohint.data );
1312
1313 /* Discard glyph slots for this face. */
1314 /* Beware! FT_Done_GlyphSlot() changes the field `face->glyph' */
1315 while ( face->glyph )
1316 FT_Done_GlyphSlot( face->glyph );
1317
1318 /* discard all sizes for this face */
1319 FT_List_Finalize( &face->sizes_list,
1320 destroy_size,
1321 memory,
1322 driver );
1323 face->size = NULL;
1324
1325 /* now discard client data */
1326 if ( face->generic.finalizer )
1327 face->generic.finalizer( face );
1328
1329 /* discard charmaps */
1330 destroy_charmaps( face, memory );
1331
1332 /* finalize format-specific stuff */
1333 if ( clazz->done_face )
1334 clazz->done_face( face );
1335
1336 /* close the stream for this face if needed */
1337 FT_Stream_Free(
1338 face->stream,
1339 ( face->face_flags & FT_FACE_FLAG_EXTERNAL_STREAM ) != 0 );
1340
1341 face->stream = NULL;
1342
1343 /* get rid of it */
1344 if ( face->internal )
1345 {
1346 FT_FREE( face->internal );
1347 }
1348 FT_FREE( face );
1349 }

1354 {
1355 FT_List_Finalize( &driver->faces_list,
1356 destroy_face,
1357 driver->root.memory,
1358 driver );
1359 }

1362 /**************************************************************************
1363 *
1364 * @Function:
1365 * find_unicode_charmap
1366 *
1367 * @Description:
1368 * This function finds a Unicode charmap, if there is one.
1369 * And if there is more than one, it tries to favour the more
1370 * extensive one, i.e., one that supports UCS-4 against those which
1371 * are limited to the BMP (said UCS-2 encoding.)
1372 *
1373 * This function is called from open_face() (just below), and also
1374 * from FT_Select_Charmap( ..., FT_ENCODING_UNICODE ).
1375 */
1376 static FT_Error
1377 find_unicode_charmap( FT_Face face )
1378 {
1379 FT_CharMap* first;
1380 FT_CharMap* cur;
1381
1382
1383 /* caller should have already checked that `face' is valid */
1384 FT_ASSERT( face );
1385
1386 first = face->charmaps;
1387
1388 if ( !first )
1389 return FT_THROW( Invalid_CharMap_Handle );
1390
1391 /*
1392 * The original TrueType specification(s) only specified charmap
1393 * formats that are capable of mapping 8 or 16 bit character codes to
1394 * glyph indices.
1395 *
1396 * However, recent updates to the Apple and OpenType specifications
1397 * introduced new formats that are capable of mapping 32-bit character
1398 * codes as well. And these are already used on some fonts, mainly to
1399 * map non-BMP Asian ideographs as defined in Unicode.
1400 *
1401 * For compatibility purposes, these fonts generally come with
1402 * *several* Unicode charmaps:
1403 *
1404 * - One of them in the "old" 16-bit format, that cannot access
1405 * all glyphs in the font.
1406 *
1407 * - Another one in the "new" 32-bit format, that can access all
1408 * the glyphs.
1409 *
1410 * This function has been written to always favor a 32-bit charmap
1411 * when found. Otherwise, a 16-bit one is returned when found.
1412 */
1413
1414 /* Since the `interesting' table, with IDs (3,10), is normally the */
1415 /* last one, we loop backwards. This loses with type1 fonts with */
1416 /* non-BMP characters (<.0001%), this wins with .ttf with non-BMP */
1417 /* chars (.01% ?), and this is the same about 99.99% of the time! */
1418
1419 cur = first + face->num_charmaps; /* points after the last one */
1420
1421 for ( ; --cur >= first; )
1422 {
1423 if ( cur[0]->encoding == FT_ENCODING_UNICODE )
1424 {
1425 /* XXX If some new encodings to represent UCS-4 are added, */
1426 /* they should be added here. */
1427 if ( ( cur[0]->platform_id == TT_PLATFORM_MICROSOFT &&
1428 cur[0]->encoding_id == TT_MS_ID_UCS_4 ) ||
1429 ( cur[0]->platform_id == TT_PLATFORM_APPLE_UNICODE &&
1430 cur[0]->encoding_id == TT_APPLE_ID_UNICODE_32 ) )
1431 {
1432 face->charmap = cur[0];
1433 return FT_Err_Ok;
1434 }
1435 }
1436 }
1437
1438 /* We do not have any UCS-4 charmap. */
1439 /* Do the loop again and search for UCS-2 charmaps. */
1440 cur = first + face->num_charmaps;
1441
1442 for ( ; --cur >= first; )
1443 {
1444 if ( cur[0]->encoding == FT_ENCODING_UNICODE )
1445 {
1446 face->charmap = cur[0];
1447 return FT_Err_Ok;
1448 }
1449 }
1450
1451 return FT_THROW( Invalid_CharMap_Handle );
1452 }
1453
1454
1455 /**************************************************************************
1456 *
1457 * @Function:
1458 * find_variant_selector_charmap
1459 *
1460 * @Description:
1461 * This function finds the variant selector charmap, if there is one.
1462 * There can only be one (platform=0, specific=5, format=14).
1463 */
1464 static FT_CharMap
1465 find_variant_selector_charmap( FT_Face face )
1466 {
1467 FT_CharMap* first;
1468 FT_CharMap* end;
1469 FT_CharMap* cur;
1470
1471
1472 /* caller should have already checked that `face' is valid */
1473 FT_ASSERT( face );
1474
1475 first = face->charmaps;
1476
1477 if ( !first )
1478 return NULL;
1479
1480 end = first + face->num_charmaps; /* points after the last one */
1481
1482 for ( cur = first; cur < end; cur++ )
1483 {
1484 if ( cur[0]->platform_id == TT_PLATFORM_APPLE_UNICODE &&
1485 cur[0]->encoding_id == TT_APPLE_ID_VARIANT_SELECTOR &&
1486 FT_Get_CMap_Format( cur[0] ) == 14 )
1487 return cur[0];
1488 }
1489
1490 return NULL;
1491 }

1494 /**************************************************************************
1495 *
1496 * @Function:
1497 * open_face
1498 *
1499 * @Description:
1500 * This function does some work for FT_Open_Face().
1501 */
1502 static FT_Error
1503 open_face( FT_Driver driver,
1504 FT_Stream *astream,
1505 FT_Bool *anexternal_stream,
1506 FT_Long face_index,
1507 FT_Int num_params,
1508 FT_Parameter* params,
1509 FT_Face *aface )
1510 {
1511 FT_Memory memory;
1512 FT_Driver_Class clazz;
1513 FT_Face face = NULL;
1514 FT_Face_Internal internal = NULL;
1515
1516 FT_Error error, error2;
1517
1518
1519 clazz = driver->clazz;
1520 memory = driver->root.memory;
1521
1522 /* allocate the face object and perform basic initialization */
1523 if ( FT_ALLOC( face, clazz->face_object_size ) )
1524 goto Fail;
1525
1526 face->driver = driver;
1527 face->memory = memory;
1528 face->stream = *astream;
1529
1530 /* set the FT_FACE_FLAG_EXTERNAL_STREAM bit for FT_Done_Face */
1531 if ( *anexternal_stream )
1532 face->face_flags |= FT_FACE_FLAG_EXTERNAL_STREAM;
1533
1534 if ( FT_NEW( internal ) )
1535 goto Fail;
1536
1537 face->internal = internal;
1538
1539#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_INCREMENTAL
1540 {
1541 int i;
1542
1543
1544 face->internal->incremental_interface = NULL;
1545 for ( i = 0; i < num_params && !face->internal->incremental_interface;
1546 i++ )
1547 if ( params[i].tag == FT_PARAM_TAG_INCREMENTAL )
1548 face->internal->incremental_interface =
1549 (FT_Incremental_Interface)params[i].data;
1550 }
1551#endif
1552
1553 face->internal->random_seed = -1;
1554
1555 if ( clazz->init_face )
1556 error = clazz->init_face( *astream,
1557 face,
1558 (FT_Int)face_index,
1559 num_params,
1560 params );
1561 /* Stream may have been changed. */
1562 *astream = face->stream;
1563 *anexternal_stream =
1564 ( face->face_flags & FT_FACE_FLAG_EXTERNAL_STREAM ) != 0;
1565 if ( error )
1566 goto Fail;
1567
1568 /* select Unicode charmap by default */
1569 error2 = find_unicode_charmap( face );
1570
1571 /* if no Unicode charmap can be found, FT_Err_Invalid_CharMap_Handle */
1572 /* is returned. */
1573
1574 /* no error should happen, but we want to play safe */
1575 if ( error2 && FT_ERR_NEQ( error2, Invalid_CharMap_Handle ) )
1576 {
1577 error = error2;
1578 goto Fail;
1579 }
1580
1581 *aface = face;
1582
1583 Fail:
1584 if ( error )
1585 {
1586 destroy_charmaps( face, memory );
1587 if ( clazz->done_face )
1588 clazz->done_face( face );
1589 FT_FREE( internal );
1590 FT_FREE( face );
1591 *aface = NULL;
1592 }
1593
1594 return error;
1595 }

1655 /* The behavior here is very similar to that in base/ftmac.c, but it */
1656 /* is designed to work on non-mac systems, so no mac specific calls. */
1657 /* */
1658 /* We look at the file and determine if it is a mac dfont file or a mac */
1659 /* resource file, or a macbinary file containing a mac resource file. */
1660 /* */
1661 /* Unlike ftmac I'm not going to look at a `FOND'. I don't really see */
1662 /* the point, especially since there may be multiple `FOND' resources. */
1663 /* Instead I'll just look for `sfnt' and `POST' resources, ordered as */
1664 /* they occur in the file. */
1665 /* */
1666 /* Note that multiple `POST' resources do not mean multiple postscript */
1667 /* fonts; they all get jammed together to make what is essentially a */
1668 /* pfb file. */
1669 /* */
1670 /* We aren't interested in `NFNT' or `FONT' bitmap resources. */
1671 /* */
1672 /* As soon as we get an `sfnt' load it into memory and pass it off to */
1673 /* FT_Open_Face. */
1674 /* */
1675 /* If we have a (set of) `POST' resources, massage them into a (memory) */
1676 /* pfb file and pass that to FT_Open_Face. (As with ftmac.c I'm not */
1677 /* going to try to save the kerning info. After all that lives in the */
1678 /* `FOND' which isn't in the file containing the `POST' resources so */
1679 /* we don't really have access to it. */

1792 /* Look up `TYP1' or `CID ' table from sfnt table directory. */
1793 /* `offset' and `length' must exclude the binary header in tables. */
1794
1795 /* Type 1 and CID-keyed font drivers should recognize sfnt-wrapped */
1796 /* format too. Here, since we can't expect that the TrueType font */
1797 /* driver is loaded unconditionally, we must parse the font by */
1798 /* ourselves. We are only interested in the name of the table and */
1799 /* the offset. */
1800
1801 static FT_Error
1802 ft_lookup_PS_in_sfnt_stream( FT_Stream stream,
1803 FT_Long face_index,
1804 FT_ULong* offset,
1805 FT_ULong* length,
1806 FT_Bool* is_sfnt_cid )
1807 {
1808 FT_Error error;
1809 FT_UShort numTables;
1810 FT_Long pstable_index;
1811 FT_ULong tag;
1812 int i;
1813
1814
1815 *offset = 0;
1816 *length = 0;
1817 *is_sfnt_cid = FALSE;
1818
1819 /* TODO: support for sfnt-wrapped PS/CID in TTC format */
1820
1821 /* version check for 'typ1' (should be ignored?) */
1822 if ( FT_READ_ULONG( tag ) )
1823 return error;
1824 if ( tag != TTAG_typ1 )
1825 return FT_THROW( Unknown_File_Format );
1826
1827 if ( FT_READ_USHORT( numTables ) )
1828 return error;
1829 if ( FT_STREAM_SKIP( 2 * 3 ) ) /* skip binary search header */
1830 return error;
1831
1832 pstable_index = -1;
1833 *is_sfnt_cid = FALSE;
1834
1835 for ( i = 0; i < numTables; i++ )
1836 {
1837 if ( FT_READ_ULONG( tag ) || FT_STREAM_SKIP( 4 ) ||
1838 FT_READ_ULONG( *offset ) || FT_READ_ULONG( *length ) )
1839 return error;
1840
1841 if ( tag == TTAG_CID )
1842 {
1843 pstable_index++;
1844 *offset += 22;
1845 *length -= 22;
1846 *is_sfnt_cid = TRUE;
1847 if ( face_index < 0 )
1848 return FT_Err_Ok;
1849 }
1850 else if ( tag == TTAG_TYP1 )
1851 {
1852 pstable_index++;
1853 *offset += 24;
1854 *length -= 24;
1855 *is_sfnt_cid = FALSE;
1856 if ( face_index < 0 )
1857 return FT_Err_Ok;
1858 }
1859 if ( face_index >= 0 && pstable_index == face_index )
1860 return FT_Err_Ok;
1861 }
1862
1863 return FT_THROW( Table_Missing );
1864 }

1866
1867 FT_LOCAL_DEF( FT_Error )
1868 open_face_PS_from_sfnt_stream( FT_Library library,
1869 FT_Stream stream,
1870 FT_Long face_index,
1871 FT_Int num_params,
1872 FT_Parameter *params,
1873 FT_Face *aface )
1874 {
1875 FT_Error error;
1876 FT_Memory memory = library->memory;
1877 FT_ULong offset, length;
1878 FT_ULong pos;
1879 FT_Bool is_sfnt_cid;
1880 FT_Byte* sfnt_ps = NULL;
1881
1882 FT_UNUSED( num_params );
1883 FT_UNUSED( params );
1884
1885
1886 /* ignore GX stuff */
1887 if ( face_index > 0 )
1888 face_index &= 0xFFFFL;
1889
1890 pos = FT_STREAM_POS();
1891
1892 error = ft_lookup_PS_in_sfnt_stream( stream,
1893 face_index,
1894 &offset,
1895 &length,
1896 &is_sfnt_cid );
1897 if ( error )
1898 goto Exit;
1899
1900 if ( offset > stream->size )
1901 {
1902 FT_TRACE2(( "open_face_PS_from_sfnt_stream: invalid table offset\n" ));
1903 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Table );
1904 goto Exit;
1905 }
1906 else if ( length > stream->size - offset )
1907 {
1908 FT_TRACE2(( "open_face_PS_from_sfnt_stream: invalid table length\n" ));
1909 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Table );
1910 goto Exit;
1911 }
1912
1913 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, pos + offset );
1914 if ( error )
1915 goto Exit;
1916
1917 if ( FT_QALLOC( sfnt_ps, (FT_Long)length ) )
1918 goto Exit;
1919
1920 error = FT_Stream_Read( stream, (FT_Byte *)sfnt_ps, length );
1921 if ( error )
1922 {
1923 FT_FREE( sfnt_ps );
1924 goto Exit;
1925 }
1926
1927 error = open_face_from_buffer( library,
1928 sfnt_ps,
1929 length,
1930 FT_MIN( face_index, 0 ),
1931 is_sfnt_cid ? "t1cid" : "type1",
1932 aface );
1933 Exit:
1934 {
1935 FT_Error error1;
1936
1937
1938 if ( FT_ERR_EQ( error, Unknown_File_Format ) )
1939 {
1940 error1 = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, pos );
1941 if ( error1 )
1942 return error1;
1943 }
1944
1945 return error;
1946 }
1947 }

1949
1950#ifndef FT_MACINTOSH
1951
1952 /* The resource header says we've got resource_cnt `POST' (type1) */
1953 /* resources in this file. They all need to be coalesced into */
1954 /* one lump which gets passed on to the type1 driver. */
1955 /* Here can be only one PostScript font in a file so face_index */
1956 /* must be 0 (or -1). */
1957 /* */
1958 static FT_Error
1959 Mac_Read_POST_Resource( FT_Library library,
1960 FT_Stream stream,
1961 FT_Long *offsets,
1962 FT_Long resource_cnt,
1963 FT_Long face_index,
1964 FT_Face *aface )
1965 {
1966 FT_Error error = FT_ERR( Cannot_Open_Resource );
1967 FT_Memory memory = library->memory;
1968
1969 FT_Byte* pfb_data = NULL;
1970 int i, type, flags;
1971 FT_ULong len;
1972 FT_ULong pfb_len, pfb_pos, pfb_lenpos;
1973 FT_ULong rlen, temp;
1974
1975
1976 if ( face_index == -1 )
1977 face_index = 0;
1978 if ( face_index != 0 )
1979 return error;
1980
1981 /* Find the length of all the POST resources, concatenated. Assume */
1982 /* worst case (each resource in its own section). */
1983 pfb_len = 0;
1984 for ( i = 0; i < resource_cnt; i++ )
1985 {
1986 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, (FT_ULong)offsets[i] );
1987 if ( error )
1988 goto Exit;
1989 if ( FT_READ_ULONG( temp ) ) /* actually LONG */
1990 goto Exit;
1991
1992 /* FT2 allocator takes signed long buffer length,
1993 * too large value causing overflow should be checked
1994 */
1995 FT_TRACE4(( " POST fragment #%d: length=0x%08lx"
1996 " total pfb_len=0x%08lx\n",
1997 i, temp, pfb_len + temp + 6 ));
1998
1999 if ( FT_MAC_RFORK_MAX_LEN < temp ||
2000 FT_MAC_RFORK_MAX_LEN - temp < pfb_len + 6 )
2001 {
2002 FT_TRACE2(( " MacOS resource length cannot exceed"
2003 " 0x%08lx\n",
2004 FT_MAC_RFORK_MAX_LEN ));
2005
2006 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Offset );
2007 goto Exit;
2008 }
2009
2010 pfb_len += temp + 6;
2011 }
2012
2013 FT_TRACE2(( " total buffer size to concatenate"
2014 " %ld POST fragments: 0x%08lx\n",
2015 resource_cnt, pfb_len + 2 ));
2016
2017 if ( pfb_len + 2 < 6 )
2018 {
2019 FT_TRACE2(( " too long fragment length makes"
2020 " pfb_len confused: pfb_len=0x%08lx\n",
2021 pfb_len ));
2022
2023 error = FT_THROW( Array_Too_Large );
2024 goto Exit;
2025 }
2026
2027 if ( FT_QALLOC( pfb_data, (FT_Long)pfb_len + 2 ) )
2028 goto Exit;
2029
2030 pfb_data[0] = 0x80;
2031 pfb_data[1] = 1; /* Ascii section */
2032 pfb_data[2] = 0; /* 4-byte length, fill in later */
2033 pfb_data[3] = 0;
2034 pfb_data[4] = 0;
2035 pfb_data[5] = 0;
2036 pfb_pos = 6;
2037 pfb_lenpos = 2;
2038
2039 len = 0;
2040 type = 1;
2041
2042 for ( i = 0; i < resource_cnt; i++ )
2043 {
2044 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, (FT_ULong)offsets[i] );
2045 if ( error )
2046 goto Exit2;
2047 if ( FT_READ_ULONG( rlen ) )
2048 goto Exit2;
2049
2050 /* FT2 allocator takes signed long buffer length,
2051 * too large fragment length causing overflow should be checked
2052 */
2053 if ( 0x7FFFFFFFUL < rlen )
2054 {
2055 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Offset );
2056 goto Exit2;
2057 }
2058
2059 if ( FT_READ_USHORT( flags ) )
2060 goto Exit2;
2061
2062 FT_TRACE3(( "POST fragment[%d]:"
2063 " offsets=0x%08lx, rlen=0x%08lx, flags=0x%04x\n",
2064 i, offsets[i], rlen, flags ));
2065
2066 error = FT_ERR( Array_Too_Large );
2067
2068 /* postpone the check of `rlen longer than buffer' */
2069 /* until `FT_Stream_Read' */
2070
2071 if ( ( flags >> 8 ) == 0 ) /* Comment, should not be loaded */
2072 {
2073 FT_TRACE3(( " Skip POST fragment #%d because it is a comment\n",
2074 i ));
2075 continue;
2076 }
2077
2078 /* the flags are part of the resource, so rlen >= 2, */
2079 /* but some fonts declare rlen = 0 for empty fragment */
2080 if ( rlen > 2 )
2081 rlen -= 2;
2082 else
2083 rlen = 0;
2084
2085 if ( ( flags >> 8 ) == type )
2086 len += rlen;
2087 else
2088 {
2089 FT_TRACE3(( " Write POST fragment #%d header (4-byte) to buffer"
2090 " %p + 0x%08lx\n",
2091 i, (void*)pfb_data, pfb_lenpos ));
2092
2093 if ( pfb_lenpos + 3 > pfb_len + 2 )
2094 goto Exit2;
2095
2096 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos ] = (FT_Byte)( len );
2097 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos + 1] = (FT_Byte)( len >> 8 );
2098 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos + 2] = (FT_Byte)( len >> 16 );
2099 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos + 3] = (FT_Byte)( len >> 24 );
2100
2101 if ( ( flags >> 8 ) == 5 ) /* End of font mark */
2102 break;
2103
2104 FT_TRACE3(( " Write POST fragment #%d header (6-byte) to buffer"
2105 " %p + 0x%08lx\n",
2106 i, (void*)pfb_data, pfb_pos ));
2107
2108 if ( pfb_pos + 6 > pfb_len + 2 )
2109 goto Exit2;
2110
2111 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 0x80;
2112
2113 type = flags >> 8;
2114 len = rlen;
2115
2116 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = (FT_Byte)type;
2117 pfb_lenpos = pfb_pos;
2118 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 0; /* 4-byte length, fill in later */
2119 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 0;
2120 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 0;
2121 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 0;
2122 }
2123
2124 if ( pfb_pos > pfb_len || pfb_pos + rlen > pfb_len )
2125 goto Exit2;
2126
2127 FT_TRACE3(( " Load POST fragment #%d (%ld byte) to buffer"
2128 " %p + 0x%08lx\n",
2129 i, rlen, (void*)pfb_data, pfb_pos ));
2130
2131 error = FT_Stream_Read( stream, (FT_Byte *)pfb_data + pfb_pos, rlen );
2132 if ( error )
2133 goto Exit2;
2134
2135 pfb_pos += rlen;
2136 }
2137
2138 error = FT_ERR( Array_Too_Large );
2139
2140 if ( pfb_pos + 2 > pfb_len + 2 )
2141 goto Exit2;
2142 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 0x80;
2143 pfb_data[pfb_pos++] = 3;
2144
2145 if ( pfb_lenpos + 3 > pfb_len + 2 )
2146 goto Exit2;
2147 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos ] = (FT_Byte)( len );
2148 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos + 1] = (FT_Byte)( len >> 8 );
2149 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos + 2] = (FT_Byte)( len >> 16 );
2150 pfb_data[pfb_lenpos + 3] = (FT_Byte)( len >> 24 );
2151
2152 return open_face_from_buffer( library,
2153 pfb_data,
2154 pfb_pos,
2155 face_index,
2156 "type1",
2157 aface );
2158
2159 Exit2:
2160 if ( FT_ERR_EQ( error, Array_Too_Large ) )
2161 FT_TRACE2(( " Abort due to too-short buffer to store"
2162 " all POST fragments\n" ));
2163 else if ( FT_ERR_EQ( error, Invalid_Offset ) )
2164 FT_TRACE2(( " Abort due to invalid offset in a POST fragment\n" ));
2165
2166 if ( error )
2167 error = FT_ERR( Cannot_Open_Resource );
2168 FT_FREE( pfb_data );
2169
2170 Exit:
2171 return error;
2172 }
2173
2174
2175 /* The resource header says we've got resource_cnt `sfnt' */
2176 /* (TrueType/OpenType) resources in this file. Look through */
2177 /* them for the one indicated by face_index, load it into mem, */
2178 /* pass it on to the truetype driver, and return it. */
2179 /* */
2180 static FT_Error
2181 Mac_Read_sfnt_Resource( FT_Library library,
2182 FT_Stream stream,
2183 FT_Long *offsets,
2184 FT_Long resource_cnt,
2185 FT_Long face_index,
2186 FT_Face *aface )
2187 {
2188 FT_Memory memory = library->memory;
2189 FT_Byte* sfnt_data = NULL;
2190 FT_Error error;
2191 FT_ULong flag_offset;
2192 FT_ULong rlen;
2193 int is_cff;
2194 FT_Long face_index_in_resource = 0;
2195
2196
2197 if ( face_index < 0 )
2198 face_index = -face_index - 1;
2199 if ( face_index >= resource_cnt )
2200 return FT_THROW( Cannot_Open_Resource );
2201
2202 flag_offset = (FT_ULong)offsets[face_index];
2203 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, flag_offset );
2204 if ( error )
2205 goto Exit;
2206
2207 if ( FT_READ_ULONG( rlen ) )
2208 goto Exit;
2209 if ( !rlen )
2210 return FT_THROW( Cannot_Open_Resource );
2211 if ( rlen > FT_MAC_RFORK_MAX_LEN )
2212 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Offset );
2213
2214 error = open_face_PS_from_sfnt_stream( library,
2215 stream,
2216 face_index,
2217 0, NULL,
2218 aface );
2219 if ( !error )
2220 goto Exit;
2221
2222 /* rewind sfnt stream before open_face_PS_from_sfnt_stream() */
2223 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, flag_offset + 4 );
2224 if ( error )
2225 goto Exit;
2226
2227 if ( FT_QALLOC( sfnt_data, rlen ) )
2228 return error;
2229 error = FT_Stream_Read( stream, (FT_Byte *)sfnt_data, rlen );
2230 if ( error )
2231 {
2232 FT_FREE( sfnt_data );
2233 goto Exit;
2234 }
2235
2236 is_cff = rlen > 4 && !ft_memcmp( sfnt_data, "OTTO", 4 );
2237 error = open_face_from_buffer( library,
2238 sfnt_data,
2239 rlen,
2240 face_index_in_resource,
2241 is_cff ? "cff" : "truetype",
2242 aface );
2243
2244 Exit:
2245 return error;
2246 }
2247
2248
2249 /* Check for a valid resource fork header, or a valid dfont */
2250 /* header. In a resource fork the first 16 bytes are repeated */
2251 /* at the location specified by bytes 4-7. In a dfont bytes */
2252 /* 4-7 point to 16 bytes of zeroes instead. */
2253 /* */
2254 static FT_Error
2255 IsMacResource( FT_Library library,
2256 FT_Stream stream,
2257 FT_Long resource_offset,
2258 FT_Long face_index,
2259 FT_Face *aface )
2260 {
2261 FT_Memory memory = library->memory;
2262 FT_Error error;
2263 FT_Long map_offset, rdata_pos;
2264 FT_Long *data_offsets;
2265 FT_Long count;
2266
2267
2268 error = FT_Raccess_Get_HeaderInfo( library, stream, resource_offset,
2269 &map_offset, &rdata_pos );
2270 if ( error )
2271 return error;
2272
2273 /* POST resources must be sorted to concatenate properly */
2274 error = FT_Raccess_Get_DataOffsets( library, stream,
2275 map_offset, rdata_pos,
2276 TTAG_POST, TRUE,
2277 &data_offsets, &count );
2278 if ( !error )
2279 {
2280 error = Mac_Read_POST_Resource( library, stream, data_offsets, count,
2281 face_index, aface );
2282 FT_FREE( data_offsets );
2283 /* POST exists in an LWFN providing a single face */
2284 if ( !error )
2285 (*aface)->num_faces = 1;
2286 return error;
2287 }
2288
2289 /* sfnt resources should not be sorted to preserve the face order by
2290 QuickDraw API */
2291 error = FT_Raccess_Get_DataOffsets( library, stream,
2292 map_offset, rdata_pos,
2293 TTAG_sfnt, FALSE,
2294 &data_offsets, &count );
2295 if ( !error )
2296 {
2297 FT_Long face_index_internal = face_index % count;
2298
2299
2300 error = Mac_Read_sfnt_Resource( library, stream, data_offsets, count,
2301 face_index_internal, aface );
2302 FT_FREE( data_offsets );
2303 if ( !error )
2304 (*aface)->num_faces = count;
2305 }
2306
2307 return error;
2308 }

2311 /* Check for a valid macbinary header, and if we find one */
2312 /* check that the (flattened) resource fork in it is valid. */
2313 /* */
2314 static FT_Error
2315 IsMacBinary( FT_Library library,
2316 FT_Stream stream,
2317 FT_Long face_index,
2318 FT_Face *aface )
2319 {
2320 unsigned char header[128];
2321 FT_Error error;
2322 FT_Long dlen, offset;
2323
2324
2325 if ( !stream )
2326 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Stream_Operation );
2327
2328 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, 0 );
2329 if ( error )
2330 goto Exit;
2331
2332 error = FT_Stream_Read( stream, (FT_Byte*)header, 128 );
2333 if ( error )
2334 goto Exit;
2335
2336 if ( header[ 0] != 0 ||
2337 header[74] != 0 ||
2338 header[82] != 0 ||
2339 header[ 1] == 0 ||
2340 header[ 1] > 33 ||
2341 header[63] != 0 ||
2342 header[2 + header[1]] != 0 ||
2343 header[0x53] > 0x7F )
2344 return FT_THROW( Unknown_File_Format );
2345
2346 dlen = ( header[0x53] << 24 ) |
2347 ( header[0x54] << 16 ) |
2348 ( header[0x55] << 8 ) |
2349 header[0x56];
2350#if 0
2351 rlen = ( header[0x57] << 24 ) |
2352 ( header[0x58] << 16 ) |
2353 ( header[0x59] << 8 ) |
2354 header[0x5A];
2355#endif /* 0 */
2356 offset = 128 + ( ( dlen + 127 ) & ~127 );
2357
2358 return IsMacResource( library, stream, offset, face_index, aface );
2359
2360 Exit:
2361 return error;
2362 }

2364
2365 static FT_Error
2366 load_face_in_embedded_rfork( FT_Library library,
2367 FT_Stream stream,
2368 FT_Long face_index,
2369 FT_Face *aface,
2370 const FT_Open_Args *args )
2371 {
2372
2373#undef FT_COMPONENT
2374#define FT_COMPONENT raccess
2375
2376 FT_Memory memory = library->memory;
2377 FT_Error error = FT_ERR( Unknown_File_Format );
2378 FT_UInt i;
2379
2380 char* file_names[FT_RACCESS_N_RULES];
2381 FT_Long offsets[FT_RACCESS_N_RULES];
2382 FT_Error errors[FT_RACCESS_N_RULES];
2383 FT_Bool is_darwin_vfs, vfs_rfork_has_no_font = FALSE; /* not tested */
2384
2385 FT_Open_Args args2;
2386 FT_Stream stream2 = NULL;
2387
2388
2389 FT_Raccess_Guess( library, stream,
2390 args->pathname, file_names, offsets, errors );
2391
2392 for ( i = 0; i < FT_RACCESS_N_RULES; i++ )
2393 {
2394 is_darwin_vfs = ft_raccess_rule_by_darwin_vfs( library, i );
2395 if ( is_darwin_vfs && vfs_rfork_has_no_font )
2396 {
2397 FT_TRACE3(( "Skip rule %d: darwin vfs resource fork"
2398 " is already checked and"
2399 " no font is found\n",
2400 i ));
2401 continue;
2402 }
2403
2404 if ( errors[i] )
2405 {
2406 FT_TRACE3(( "Error 0x%x has occurred in rule %d\n",
2407 errors[i], i ));
2408 continue;
2409 }
2410
2411 args2.flags = FT_OPEN_PATHNAME;
2412 args2.pathname = file_names[i] ? file_names[i] : args->pathname;
2413
2414 FT_TRACE3(( "Try rule %d: %s (offset=%ld) ...",
2415 i, args2.pathname, offsets[i] ));
2416
2417 error = FT_Stream_New( library, &args2, &stream2 );
2418 if ( is_darwin_vfs && FT_ERR_EQ( error, Cannot_Open_Stream ) )
2419 vfs_rfork_has_no_font = TRUE;
2420
2421 if ( error )
2422 {
2423 FT_TRACE3(( "failed\n" ));
2424 continue;
2425 }
2426
2427 error = IsMacResource( library, stream2, offsets[i],
2428 face_index, aface );
2429 FT_Stream_Free( stream2, 0 );
2430
2431 FT_TRACE3(( "%s\n", error ? "failed": "successful" ));
2432
2433 if ( !error )
2434 break;
2435 else if ( is_darwin_vfs )
2436 vfs_rfork_has_no_font = TRUE;
2437 }
2438
2439 for (i = 0; i < FT_RACCESS_N_RULES; i++)
2440 {
2441 if ( file_names[i] )
2442 FT_FREE( file_names[i] );
2443 }
2444
2445 /* Caller (load_mac_face) requires FT_Err_Unknown_File_Format. */
2446 if ( error )
2447 error = FT_ERR( Unknown_File_Format );
2448
2449 return error;
2450
2451#undef FT_COMPONENT
2452#define FT_COMPONENT objs
2453
2454 }
2455
2456
2457 /* Check for some macintosh formats without Carbon framework. */
2458 /* Is this a macbinary file? If so look at the resource fork. */
2459 /* Is this a mac dfont file? */
2460 /* Is this an old style resource fork? (in data) */
2461 /* Else call load_face_in_embedded_rfork to try extra rules */
2462 /* (defined in `ftrfork.c'). */
2463 /* */
2464 static FT_Error
2465 load_mac_face( FT_Library library,
2466 FT_Stream stream,
2467 FT_Long face_index,
2468 FT_Face *aface,
2469 const FT_Open_Args *args )
2470 {
2471 FT_Error error;
2472 FT_UNUSED( args );
2473
2474
2475 error = IsMacBinary( library, stream, face_index, aface );
2476 if ( FT_ERR_EQ( error, Unknown_File_Format ) )
2477 {
2478
2479#undef FT_COMPONENT
2480#define FT_COMPONENT raccess
2481
2482#ifdef FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_TRACE
2483 FT_TRACE3(( "Try as dfont: " ));
2484 if ( !( args->flags & FT_OPEN_MEMORY ) )
2485 FT_TRACE3(( "%s ...", args->pathname ));
2486#endif
2487
2488 error = IsMacResource( library, stream, 0, face_index, aface );
2489
2490 FT_TRACE3(( "%s\n", error ? "failed" : "successful" ));
2491
2492#undef FT_COMPONENT
2493#define FT_COMPONENT objs
2494
2495 }
2496
2497 if ( ( FT_ERR_EQ( error, Unknown_File_Format ) ||
2498 FT_ERR_EQ( error, Invalid_Stream_Operation ) ) &&
2499 ( args->flags & FT_OPEN_PATHNAME ) )
2500 error = load_face_in_embedded_rfork( library, stream,
2501 face_index, aface, args );
2502 return error;
2503 }
2504#endif
2505
2506#endif /* !FT_MACINTOSH && FT_CONFIG_OPTION_MAC_FONTS */

2520
2521 static FT_Error
2522 ft_open_face_internal( FT_Library library,
2523 const FT_Open_Args* args,
2524 FT_Long face_index,
2525 FT_Face *aface,
2526 FT_Bool test_mac_fonts )
2527 {
2528 FT_Error error;
2529 FT_Driver driver = NULL;
2530 FT_Memory memory = NULL;
2531 FT_Stream stream = NULL;
2532 FT_Face face = NULL;
2533 FT_ListNode node = NULL;
2534 FT_Bool external_stream;
2535 FT_Module* cur;
2536 FT_Module* limit;
2537
2538#ifndef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_MAC_FONTS
2539 FT_UNUSED( test_mac_fonts );
2540#endif
2541
2542
2543 /* only use lower 31 bits together with sign bit */
2544 if ( face_index > 0 )
2545 face_index &= 0x7FFFFFFFL;
2546 else
2547 {
2548 face_index = -face_index;
2549 face_index &= 0x7FFFFFFFL;
2550 face_index = -face_index;
2551 }
2552
2553#ifdef FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_TRACE
2554 FT_TRACE3(( "FT_Open_Face: " ));
2555 if ( face_index < 0 )
2556 FT_TRACE3(( "Requesting number of faces and named instances\n"));
2557 else
2558 {
2559 FT_TRACE3(( "Requesting face %ld", face_index & 0xFFFFL ));
2560 if ( face_index & 0x7FFF0000L )
2561 FT_TRACE3(( ", named instance %ld", face_index >> 16 ));
2562 FT_TRACE3(( "\n" ));
2563 }
2564#endif
2565
2566 /* test for valid `library' delayed to `FT_Stream_New' */
2567
2568 if ( !args )
2569 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
2570
2571 external_stream = FT_BOOL( ( args->flags & FT_OPEN_STREAM ) &&
2572 args->stream );
2573
2574 /* create input stream */
2575 error = FT_Stream_New( library, args, &stream );
2576 if ( error )
2577 goto Fail3;
2578
2579 /* Do this error check after `FT_Stream_New` to ensure that the */
2580 /* 'close' callback is called. */
2581 if ( !aface && face_index >= 0 )
2582 {
2583 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
2584 goto Fail3;
2585 }
2586
2587 memory = library->memory;
2588
2589 /* If the font driver is specified in the `args' structure, use */
2590 /* it. Otherwise, we scan the list of registered drivers. */
2591 if ( ( args->flags & FT_OPEN_DRIVER ) && args->driver )
2592 {
2593 driver = FT_DRIVER( args->driver );
2594
2595 /* not all modules are drivers, so check... */
2596 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_DRIVER( driver ) )
2597 {
2598 FT_Int num_params = 0;
2599 FT_Parameter* params = NULL;
2600
2601
2602 if ( args->flags & FT_OPEN_PARAMS )
2603 {
2604 num_params = args->num_params;
2605 params = args->params;
2606 }
2607
2608 error = open_face( driver, &stream, &external_stream, face_index,
2609 num_params, params, &face );
2610 if ( !error )
2611 goto Success;
2612 }
2613 else
2614 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Handle );
2615
2616 FT_Stream_Free( stream, external_stream );
2617 goto Fail;
2618 }
2619 else
2620 {
2621 error = FT_ERR( Missing_Module );
2622
2623 /* check each font driver for an appropriate format */
2624 cur = library->modules;
2625 limit = cur + library->num_modules;
2626
2627 for ( ; cur < limit; cur++ )
2628 {
2629 /* not all modules are font drivers, so check... */
2630 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_DRIVER( cur[0] ) )
2631 {
2632 FT_Int num_params = 0;
2633 FT_Parameter* params = NULL;
2634
2635
2636 driver = FT_DRIVER( cur[0] );
2637
2638 if ( args->flags & FT_OPEN_PARAMS )
2639 {
2640 num_params = args->num_params;
2641 params = args->params;
2642 }
2643
2644 error = open_face( driver, &stream, &external_stream, face_index,
2645 num_params, params, &face );
2646 if ( !error )
2647 goto Success;
2648
2649#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_MAC_FONTS
2650 if ( test_mac_fonts &&
2651 ft_strcmp( cur[0]->clazz->module_name, "truetype" ) == 0 &&
2652 FT_ERR_EQ( error, Table_Missing ) )
2653 {
2654 /* TrueType but essential tables are missing */
2655 error = FT_Stream_Seek( stream, 0 );
2656 if ( error )
2657 break;
2658
2659 error = open_face_PS_from_sfnt_stream( library,
2660 stream,
2661 face_index,
2662 num_params,
2663 params,
2664 aface );
2665 if ( !error )
2666 {
2667 FT_Stream_Free( stream, external_stream );
2668 return error;
2669 }
2670 }
2671#endif
2672
2673 if ( FT_ERR_NEQ( error, Unknown_File_Format ) )
2674 goto Fail3;
2675 }
2676 }
2677
2678 Fail3:
2679 /* If we are on the mac, and we get an */
2680 /* FT_Err_Invalid_Stream_Operation it may be because we have an */
2681 /* empty data fork, so we need to check the resource fork. */
2682 if ( FT_ERR_NEQ( error, Cannot_Open_Stream ) &&
2683 FT_ERR_NEQ( error, Unknown_File_Format ) &&
2684 FT_ERR_NEQ( error, Invalid_Stream_Operation ) )
2685 goto Fail2;
2686
2687#if !defined( FT_MACINTOSH ) && defined( FT_CONFIG_OPTION_MAC_FONTS )
2688 if ( test_mac_fonts )
2689 {
2690 error = load_mac_face( library, stream, face_index, aface, args );
2691 if ( !error )
2692 {
2693 /* We don't want to go to Success here. We've already done */
2694 /* that. On the other hand, if we succeeded we still need to */
2695 /* close this stream (we opened a different stream which */
2696 /* extracted the interesting information out of this stream */
2697 /* here. That stream will still be open and the face will */
2698 /* point to it). */
2699 FT_Stream_Free( stream, external_stream );
2700 return error;
2701 }
2702 }
2703
2704 if ( FT_ERR_NEQ( error, Unknown_File_Format ) )
2705 goto Fail2;
2706#endif /* !FT_MACINTOSH && FT_CONFIG_OPTION_MAC_FONTS */
2707
2708 /* no driver is able to handle this format */
2709 error = FT_THROW( Unknown_File_Format );
2710
2711 Fail2:
2712 FT_Stream_Free( stream, external_stream );
2713 goto Fail;
2714 }
2715
2716 Success:
2717 FT_TRACE4(( "FT_Open_Face: New face object, adding to list\n" ));
2718
2719 /* add the face object to its driver's list */
2720 if ( FT_QNEW( node ) )
2721 goto Fail;
2722
2723 node->data = face;
2724 /* don't assume driver is the same as face->driver, so use */
2725 /* face->driver instead. */
2726 FT_List_Add( &face->driver->faces_list, node );
2727
2728 /* now allocate a glyph slot object for the face */
2729 FT_TRACE4(( "FT_Open_Face: Creating glyph slot\n" ));
2730
2731 if ( face_index >= 0 )
2732 {
2733 error = FT_New_GlyphSlot( face, NULL );
2734 if ( error )
2735 goto Fail;
2736
2737 /* finally, allocate a size object for the face */
2738 {
2739 FT_Size size;
2740
2741
2742 FT_TRACE4(( "FT_Open_Face: Creating size object\n" ));
2743
2744 error = FT_New_Size( face, &size );
2745 if ( error )
2746 goto Fail;
2747
2748 face->size = size;
2749 }
2750 }
2751
2752 /* some checks */
2753
2754 if ( FT_IS_SCALABLE( face ) )
2755 {
2756 if ( face->height < 0 )
2757 face->height = (FT_Short)-face->height;
2758
2759 if ( !FT_HAS_VERTICAL( face ) )
2760 face->max_advance_height = (FT_Short)face->height;
2761 }
2762
2763 if ( FT_HAS_FIXED_SIZES( face ) )
2764 {
2765 FT_Int i;
2766
2767
2768 for ( i = 0; i < face->num_fixed_sizes; i++ )
2769 {
2770 FT_Bitmap_Size* bsize = face->available_sizes + i;
2771
2772
2773 if ( bsize->height < 0 )
2774 bsize->height = -bsize->height;
2775 if ( bsize->x_ppem < 0 )
2776 bsize->x_ppem = -bsize->x_ppem;
2777 if ( bsize->y_ppem < 0 )
2778 bsize->y_ppem = -bsize->y_ppem;
2779
2780 /* check whether negation actually has worked */
2781 if ( bsize->height < 0 || bsize->x_ppem < 0 || bsize->y_ppem < 0 )
2782 {
2783 FT_TRACE0(( "FT_Open_Face:"
2784 " Invalid bitmap dimensions for strike %d,"
2785 " now disabled\n", i ));
2786 bsize->width = 0;
2787 bsize->height = 0;
2788 bsize->size = 0;
2789 bsize->x_ppem = 0;
2790 bsize->y_ppem = 0;
2791 }
2792 }
2793 }
2794
2795 /* initialize internal face data */
2796 {
2797 FT_Face_Internal internal = face->internal;
2798
2799
2800 internal->transform_matrix.xx = 0x10000L;
2801 internal->transform_matrix.xy = 0;
2802 internal->transform_matrix.yx = 0;
2803 internal->transform_matrix.yy = 0x10000L;
2804
2805 internal->transform_delta.x = 0;
2806 internal->transform_delta.y = 0;
2807
2808 internal->refcount = 1;
2809
2810 internal->no_stem_darkening = -1;
2811
2812#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SUBPIXEL_RENDERING
2813 /* Per-face filtering can only be set up by FT_Face_Properties */
2814 internal->lcd_filter_func = NULL;
2815#endif
2816 }
2817
2818 if ( aface )
2819 *aface = face;
2820 else
2821 FT_Done_Face( face );
2822
2823 goto Exit;
2824
2825 Fail:
2826 if ( node )
2827 FT_Done_Face( face ); /* face must be in the driver's list */
2828 else if ( face )
2829 destroy_face( memory, face, driver );
2830
2831 Exit:
2832#ifdef FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_TRACE
2833 if ( !error && face_index < 0 )
2834 {
2835 FT_TRACE3(( "FT_Open_Face: The font has %ld face%s\n",
2836 face->num_faces,
2837 face->num_faces == 1 ? "" : "s" ));
2838 FT_TRACE3(( " and %ld named instance%s for face %ld\n",
2839 face->style_flags >> 16,
2840 ( face->style_flags >> 16 ) == 1 ? "" : "s",
2841 -face_index - 1 ));
2842 }
2843#endif
2844
2845 FT_TRACE4(( "FT_Open_Face: Return 0x%x\n", error ));
2846
2847 return error;
2848 }

2933 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
2934 FT_Done_Face( FT_Face face )
2935 {
2936 FT_Error error;
2937 FT_Driver driver;
2938 FT_Memory memory;
2939 FT_ListNode node;
2940
2941
2942 error = FT_ERR( Invalid_Face_Handle );
2943 if ( face && face->driver )
2944 {
2945 face->internal->refcount--;
2946 if ( face->internal->refcount > 0 )
2947 error = FT_Err_Ok;

2958 FT_List_Remove( &driver->faces_list, node );

3040
3041 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
3042 FT_Done_Size( FT_Size size )
3043 {
3044 FT_Error error;
3045 FT_Driver driver;
3046 FT_Memory memory;
3047 FT_Face face;
3048 FT_ListNode node;
3049
3050
3051 if ( !size )
3052 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Size_Handle );
3053
3054 face = size->face;
3055 if ( !face )
3056 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Face_Handle );
3057
3058 driver = face->driver;
3059 if ( !driver )
3060 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Driver_Handle );
3061
3062 memory = driver->root.memory;
3063
3064 error = FT_Err_Ok;
3065 node = FT_List_Find( &face->sizes_list, size );
3066 if ( node )
3067 {
3068 FT_List_Remove( &face->sizes_list, node );
3069 FT_FREE( node );
3070
3071 if ( face->size == size )
3072 {
3073 face->size = NULL;
3074 if ( face->sizes_list.head )
3075 face->size = (FT_Size)(face->sizes_list.head->data);
3076 }
3077
3078 destroy_size( memory, size, driver );
3079 }
3080 else
3081 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Size_Handle );
3082
3083 return error;
3084 }

3088
3089 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
3090 FT_Match_Size( FT_Face face,
3091 FT_Size_Request req,
3092 FT_Bool ignore_width,
3093 FT_ULong* size_index )
3094 {
3095 FT_Int i;
3096 FT_Long w, h;
3097
3098
3099 if ( !FT_HAS_FIXED_SIZES( face ) )
3100 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Face_Handle );
3101
3102 /* FT_Bitmap_Size doesn't provide enough info... */
3103 if ( req->type != FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_NOMINAL )
3104 return FT_THROW( Unimplemented_Feature );
3105
3106 w = FT_REQUEST_WIDTH ( req );
3107 h = FT_REQUEST_HEIGHT( req );
3108
3109 if ( req->width && !req->height )
3110 h = w;
3111 else if ( !req->width && req->height )
3112 w = h;
3113
3114 w = FT_PIX_ROUND( w );
3115 h = FT_PIX_ROUND( h );
3116
3117 if ( !w || !h )
3118 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Pixel_Size );
3119
3120 for ( i = 0; i < face->num_fixed_sizes; i++ )
3121 {
3122 FT_Bitmap_Size* bsize = face->available_sizes + i;
3123
3124
3125 if ( h != FT_PIX_ROUND( bsize->y_ppem ) )
3126 continue;
3127
3128 if ( w == FT_PIX_ROUND( bsize->x_ppem ) || ignore_width )
3129 {
3130 FT_TRACE3(( "FT_Match_Size: bitmap strike %d matches\n", i ));
3131
3132 if ( size_index )
3133 *size_index = (FT_ULong)i;
3134
3135 return FT_Err_Ok;
3136 }
3137 }
3138
3139 FT_TRACE3(( "FT_Match_Size: no matching bitmap strike\n" ));
3140
3141 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Pixel_Size );
3142 }

3146
3147 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
3148 ft_synthesize_vertical_metrics( FT_Glyph_Metrics* metrics,
3149 FT_Pos advance )
3150 {
3151 FT_Pos height = metrics->height;
3152
3153
3154 /* compensate for glyph with bbox above/below the baseline */
3155 if ( metrics->horiBearingY < 0 )
3156 {
3157 if ( height < metrics->horiBearingY )
3158 height = metrics->horiBearingY;
3159 }
3160 else if ( metrics->horiBearingY > 0 )
3161 height -= metrics->horiBearingY;
3162
3163 /* the factor 1.2 is a heuristical value */
3164 if ( !advance )
3165 advance = height * 12 / 10;
3166
3167 metrics->vertBearingX = metrics->horiBearingX - metrics->horiAdvance / 2;
3168 metrics->vertBearingY = ( advance - height ) / 2;
3169 metrics->vertAdvance = advance;
3170 }

3173 static void
3174 ft_recompute_scaled_metrics( FT_Face face,
3175 FT_Size_Metrics* metrics )
3176 {
3177 /* Compute root ascender, descender, test height, and max_advance */
3178
3179#ifdef GRID_FIT_METRICS
3180 metrics->ascender = FT_PIX_CEIL( FT_MulFix( face->ascender,
3181 metrics->y_scale ) );
3182
3183 metrics->descender = FT_PIX_FLOOR( FT_MulFix( face->descender,
3184 metrics->y_scale ) );
3185
3186 metrics->height = FT_PIX_ROUND( FT_MulFix( face->height,
3187 metrics->y_scale ) );
3188
3189 metrics->max_advance = FT_PIX_ROUND( FT_MulFix( face->max_advance_width,
3190 metrics->x_scale ) );
3191#else /* !GRID_FIT_METRICS */
3192 metrics->ascender = FT_MulFix( face->ascender,
3193 metrics->y_scale );
3194
3195 metrics->descender = FT_MulFix( face->descender,
3196 metrics->y_scale );
3197
3198 metrics->height = FT_MulFix( face->height,
3199 metrics->y_scale );
3200
3201 metrics->max_advance = FT_MulFix( face->max_advance_width,
3202 metrics->x_scale );
3203#endif /* !GRID_FIT_METRICS */
3204 }

3207 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
3208 FT_Select_Metrics( FT_Face face,
3209 FT_ULong strike_index )
3210 {
3211 FT_Size_Metrics* metrics;
3212 FT_Bitmap_Size* bsize;
3213
3214
3215 metrics = &face->size->metrics;
3216 bsize = face->available_sizes + strike_index;
3217
3218 metrics->x_ppem = (FT_UShort)( ( bsize->x_ppem + 32 ) >> 6 );
3219 metrics->y_ppem = (FT_UShort)( ( bsize->y_ppem + 32 ) >> 6 );
3220
3221 if ( FT_IS_SCALABLE( face ) )
3222 {
3223 metrics->x_scale = FT_DivFix( bsize->x_ppem,
3224 face->units_per_EM );
3225 metrics->y_scale = FT_DivFix( bsize->y_ppem,
3226 face->units_per_EM );
3227
3228 ft_recompute_scaled_metrics( face, metrics );
3229 }
3230 else
3231 {
3232 metrics->x_scale = 1L << 16;
3233 metrics->y_scale = 1L << 16;
3234 metrics->ascender = bsize->y_ppem;
3235 metrics->descender = 0;
3236 metrics->height = bsize->height << 6;
3237 metrics->max_advance = bsize->x_ppem;
3238 }
3239 }

3242 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
3243 FT_Request_Metrics( FT_Face face,
3244 FT_Size_Request req )
3245 {
3246 FT_Error error = FT_Err_Ok;
3247
3248 FT_Size_Metrics* metrics;
3249
3250
3251 metrics = &face->size->metrics;
3252
3253 if ( FT_IS_SCALABLE( face ) )
3254 {
3255 FT_Long w = 0, h = 0, scaled_w = 0, scaled_h = 0;
3256
3257
3258 switch ( req->type )
3259 {
3260 case FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_NOMINAL:
3261 w = h = face->units_per_EM;
3262 break;
3263
3264 case FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_REAL_DIM:
3265 w = h = face->ascender - face->descender;
3266 break;
3267
3268 case FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_BBOX:
3269 w = face->bbox.xMax - face->bbox.xMin;
3270 h = face->bbox.yMax - face->bbox.yMin;
3271 break;
3272
3273 case FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_CELL:
3274 w = face->max_advance_width;
3275 h = face->ascender - face->descender;
3276 break;
3277
3278 case FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_SCALES:
3279 metrics->x_scale = (FT_Fixed)req->width;
3280 metrics->y_scale = (FT_Fixed)req->height;
3281 if ( !metrics->x_scale )
3282 metrics->x_scale = metrics->y_scale;
3283 else if ( !metrics->y_scale )
3284 metrics->y_scale = metrics->x_scale;
3285 goto Calculate_Ppem;
3286
3287 case FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_MAX:
3288 break;
3289 }
3290
3291 /* to be on the safe side */
3292 if ( w < 0 )
3293 w = -w;
3294
3295 if ( h < 0 )
3296 h = -h;
3297
3298 scaled_w = FT_REQUEST_WIDTH ( req );
3299 scaled_h = FT_REQUEST_HEIGHT( req );
3300
3301 /* determine scales */
3302 if ( req->height || !req->width )
3303 {
3304 if ( h == 0 )
3305 {
3306 FT_ERROR(( "FT_Request_Metrics: Divide by zero\n" ));
3307 error = FT_ERR( Divide_By_Zero );
3308 goto Exit;
3309 }
3310
3311 metrics->y_scale = FT_DivFix( scaled_h, h );
3312 }
3313
3314 if ( req->width )
3315 {
3316 if ( w == 0 )
3317 {
3318 FT_ERROR(( "FT_Request_Metrics: Divide by zero\n" ));
3319 error = FT_ERR( Divide_By_Zero );
3320 goto Exit;
3321 }
3322
3323 metrics->x_scale = FT_DivFix( scaled_w, w );
3324 }
3325 else
3326 {
3327 metrics->x_scale = metrics->y_scale;
3328 scaled_w = FT_MulDiv( scaled_h, w, h );
3329 }
3330
3331 if ( !req->height )
3332 {
3333 metrics->y_scale = metrics->x_scale;
3334 scaled_h = FT_MulDiv( scaled_w, h, w );
3335 }
3336
3337 if ( req->type == FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_CELL )
3338 {
3339 if ( metrics->y_scale > metrics->x_scale )
3340 metrics->y_scale = metrics->x_scale;
3341 else
3342 metrics->x_scale = metrics->y_scale;
3343 }
3344
3345 Calculate_Ppem:
3346 /* calculate the ppems */
3347 if ( req->type != FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_NOMINAL )
3348 {
3349 scaled_w = FT_MulFix( face->units_per_EM, metrics->x_scale );
3350 scaled_h = FT_MulFix( face->units_per_EM, metrics->y_scale );
3351 }
3352
3353 scaled_w = ( scaled_w + 32 ) >> 6;
3354 scaled_h = ( scaled_h + 32 ) >> 6;
3355 if ( scaled_w > (FT_Long)FT_USHORT_MAX ||
3356 scaled_h > (FT_Long)FT_USHORT_MAX )
3357 {
3358 FT_ERROR(( "FT_Request_Metrics: Resulting ppem size too large\n" ));
3359 error = FT_ERR( Invalid_Pixel_Size );
3360 goto Exit;
3361 }
3362
3363 metrics->x_ppem = (FT_UShort)scaled_w;
3364 metrics->y_ppem = (FT_UShort)scaled_h;
3365
3366 ft_recompute_scaled_metrics( face, metrics );
3367 }
3368 else
3369 {
3370 FT_ZERO( metrics );
3371 metrics->x_scale = 1L << 16;
3372 metrics->y_scale = 1L << 16;
3373 }
3374
3375 Exit:
3376 return error;
3377 }

3446 FT_ULong strike_index;
3447
3448
3449 if ( !face )
3450 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Face_Handle );
3451
3452 if ( !face->size )
3453 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Size_Handle );
3454
3455 if ( !req || req->width < 0 || req->height < 0 ||
3456 req->type >= FT_SIZE_REQUEST_TYPE_MAX )
3457 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
3458
3459 /* signal the auto-hinter to recompute its size metrics */
3460 /* (if requested) */
3461 face->size->internal->autohint_metrics.x_scale = 0;
3462
3463 clazz = face->driver->clazz;
3464
3465 if ( clazz->request_size )
3466 {
3467 error = clazz->request_size( face->size, req );
3468
3469 FT_TRACE5(( "FT_Request_Size (%s driver):\n",
3470 face->driver->root.clazz->module_name ));
3471 }
3472 else if ( !FT_IS_SCALABLE( face ) && FT_HAS_FIXED_SIZES( face ) )
3473 {
3474 /*
3475 * The reason that a driver doesn't have `request_size' defined is
3476 * either that the scaling here suffices or that the supported formats
3477 * are bitmap-only and size matching is not implemented.
3478 *
3479 * In the latter case, a simple size matching is done.
3480 */
3481 error = FT_Match_Size( face, req, 0, &strike_index );

3493 FT_TRACE5(( "FT_Request_Size:\n" ));

3499
3500

3715 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
3716 FT_Select_Charmap( FT_Face face,
3717 FT_Encoding encoding )
3718 {
3719 FT_CharMap* cur;
3720 FT_CharMap* limit;
3721
3722
3723 if ( !face )
3724 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Face_Handle );
3725
3726 /* FT_ENCODING_NONE is a valid encoding for BDF, PCF, and Windows FNT */
3727 if ( encoding == FT_ENCODING_NONE && !face->num_charmaps )
3728 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
3729
3730 /* FT_ENCODING_UNICODE is special. We try to find the `best' Unicode */
3731 /* charmap available, i.e., one with UCS-4 characters, if possible. */
3732 /* */
3733 /* This is done by find_unicode_charmap() above, to share code. */
3734 if ( encoding == FT_ENCODING_UNICODE )
3735 return find_unicode_charmap( face );
3736
3737 cur = face->charmaps;
3738 if ( !cur )
3739 return FT_THROW( Invalid_CharMap_Handle );
3740
3741 limit = cur + face->num_charmaps;
3742
3743 for ( ; cur < limit; cur++ )
3744 {
3745 if ( cur[0]->encoding == encoding )
3746 {
3747 face->charmap = cur[0];
3748 return FT_Err_Ok;
3749 }
3750 }
3751
3752 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
3753 }

3796
3797 if ( !charmap || !charmap->face )
3798 return -1;
3799
3800 for ( i = 0; i < charmap->face->num_charmaps; i++ )
3801 if ( charmap->face->charmaps[i] == charmap )
3802 break;
3803
3804 FT_ASSERT( i < charmap->face->num_charmaps );
3805
3806 return i;
3807 }
3808
3809
3810 static void
3811 ft_cmap_done_internal( FT_CMap cmap )
3812 {
3813 FT_CMap_Class clazz = cmap->clazz;
3814 FT_Face face = cmap->charmap.face;
3815 FT_Memory memory = FT_FACE_MEMORY( face );
3816
3817
3818 if ( clazz->done )
3819 clazz->done( cmap );
3820
3821 FT_FREE( cmap );
3822 }
3823
3824
3825 FT_BASE_DEF( void )
3826 FT_CMap_Done( FT_CMap cmap )
3827 {
3828 if ( cmap )
3829 {
3830 FT_Face face = cmap->charmap.face;
3831 FT_Memory memory = FT_FACE_MEMORY( face );
3832 FT_Error error;
3833 FT_Int i, j;
3834
3835
3836 for ( i = 0; i < face->num_charmaps; i++ )
3837 {
3838 if ( (FT_CMap)face->charmaps[i] == cmap )
3839 {
3840 FT_CharMap last_charmap = face->charmaps[face->num_charmaps - 1];
3841
3842
3843 if ( FT_QRENEW_ARRAY( face->charmaps,
3844 face->num_charmaps,
3845 face->num_charmaps - 1 ) )
3846 return;
3847
3848 /* remove it from our list of charmaps */
3849 for ( j = i + 1; j < face->num_charmaps; j++ )
3850 {
3851 if ( j == face->num_charmaps - 1 )
3852 face->charmaps[j - 1] = last_charmap;
3853 else
3854 face->charmaps[j - 1] = face->charmaps[j];
3855 }
3856
3857 face->num_charmaps--;
3858
3859 if ( (FT_CMap)face->charmap == cmap )
3860 face->charmap = NULL;
3861
3862 ft_cmap_done_internal( cmap );
3863
3864 break;
3865 }
3866 }
3867 }
3868 }

3871 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
3872 FT_CMap_New( FT_CMap_Class clazz,
3873 FT_Pointer init_data,
3874 FT_CharMap charmap,
3875 FT_CMap *acmap )
3876 {
3877 FT_Error error;
3878 FT_Face face;
3879 FT_Memory memory;
3880 FT_CMap cmap = NULL;
3881
3882
3883 if ( !clazz || !charmap || !charmap->face )
3884 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
3885
3886 face = charmap->face;
3887 memory = FT_FACE_MEMORY( face );
3888
3889 if ( !FT_ALLOC( cmap, clazz->size ) )
3890 {
3891 cmap->charmap = *charmap;
3892 cmap->clazz = clazz;
3893
3894 if ( clazz->init )
3895 {
3896 error = clazz->init( cmap, init_data );
3897 if ( error )
3898 goto Fail;
3899 }
3900
3901 /* add it to our list of charmaps */
3902 if ( FT_QRENEW_ARRAY( face->charmaps,
3903 face->num_charmaps,
3904 face->num_charmaps + 1 ) )
3905 goto Fail;
3906
3907 face->charmaps[face->num_charmaps++] = (FT_CharMap)cmap;
3908 }
3909
3910 Exit:
3911 if ( acmap )
3912 *acmap = cmap;
3913
3914 return error;
3915
3916 Fail:
3917 ft_cmap_done_internal( cmap );
3918 cmap = NULL;
3919 goto Exit;
3920 }

4012 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
4013 FT_Face_Properties( FT_Face face,
4014 FT_UInt num_properties,
4015 FT_Parameter* properties )
4016 {
4017 FT_Error error = FT_Err_Ok;
4018
4019
4020 if ( num_properties > 0 && !properties )
4021 {
4022 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
4023 goto Exit;
4024 }
4025
4026 for ( ; num_properties > 0; num_properties-- )
4027 {
4028 if ( properties->tag == FT_PARAM_TAG_STEM_DARKENING )
4029 {
4030 if ( properties->data )
4031 {
4032 if ( *( (FT_Bool*)properties->data ) == TRUE )
4033 face->internal->no_stem_darkening = FALSE;
4034 else
4035 face->internal->no_stem_darkening = TRUE;
4036 }
4037 else
4038 {
4039 /* use module default */
4040 face->internal->no_stem_darkening = -1;
4041 }
4042 }
4043 else if ( properties->tag == FT_PARAM_TAG_LCD_FILTER_WEIGHTS )
4044 {
4045#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SUBPIXEL_RENDERING
4046 if ( properties->data )
4047 {
4048 ft_memcpy( face->internal->lcd_weights,
4049 properties->data,
4050 FT_LCD_FILTER_FIVE_TAPS );
4051 face->internal->lcd_filter_func = ft_lcd_filter_fir;
4052 }
4053#else
4054 error = FT_THROW( Unimplemented_Feature );
4055 goto Exit;
4056#endif
4057 }
4058 else if ( properties->tag == FT_PARAM_TAG_RANDOM_SEED )
4059 {
4060 if ( properties->data )
4061 {
4062 face->internal->random_seed = *( (FT_Int32*)properties->data );
4063 if ( face->internal->random_seed < 0 )
4064 face->internal->random_seed = 0;
4065 }
4066 else
4067 {
4068 /* use module default */
4069 face->internal->random_seed = -1;
4070 }
4071 }
4072 else
4073 {
4074 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
4075 goto Exit;
4076 }
4077
4078 if ( error )
4079 break;
4080
4081 properties++;
4082 }
4083
4084 Exit:
4085 return error;
4086 }

4520 /* lookup a renderer by glyph format in the library's list */
4521 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Renderer )
4522 FT_Lookup_Renderer( FT_Library library,
4523 FT_Glyph_Format format,
4524 FT_ListNode* node )
4525 {
4526 FT_ListNode cur;
4527 FT_Renderer result = NULL;
4528
4529
4530 if ( !library )
4531 goto Exit;
4532
4533 cur = library->renderers.head;
4534
4535 if ( node )
4536 {
4537 if ( *node )
4538 cur = (*node)->next;
4539 *node = NULL;
4540 }
4541
4542 while ( cur )
4543 {
4544 FT_Renderer renderer = FT_RENDERER( cur->data );
4545
4546
4547 if ( renderer->glyph_format == format )
4548 {
4549 if ( node )
4550 *node = cur;
4551
4552 result = renderer;
4553 break;
4554 }
4555 cur = cur->next;
4556 }
4557
4558 Exit:
4559 return result;
4560 }
