4588
4589 static FT_Error
4590 ft_add_renderer( FT_Module module )
4591 {
4592 FT_Library library = module->library;
4593 FT_Memory memory = library->memory;
4594 FT_Error error;
4595 FT_ListNode node = NULL;
4596
4597
4598 if ( FT_QNEW( node ) )
4599 goto Exit;
4600
4601 {
4602 FT_Renderer render = FT_RENDERER( module );
4603 FT_Renderer_Class* clazz = (FT_Renderer_Class*)module->clazz;
4604
4605
4606 render->clazz = clazz;
4607 render->glyph_format = clazz->glyph_format;
4608
4609 /* allocate raster object if needed */
4610 if ( clazz->raster_class && clazz->raster_class->raster_new )
4611 {
4612 error = clazz->raster_class->raster_new( memory, &render->raster );
4613 if ( error )
4614 goto Fail;
4615
4616 render->raster_render = clazz->raster_class->raster_render;
4617 render->render = clazz->render_glyph;
4618 }
4619
4620#ifdef FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SVG
4621 if ( clazz->glyph_format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_SVG )
4622 render->render = clazz->render_glyph;
4623#endif
4624
4625 /* add to list */
4626 node->data = module;
4627 FT_List_Add( &library->renderers, node );
4628
4629 ft_set_current_renderer( library );
4630 }
4631
4632 Fail:
4633 if ( error )
4634 FT_FREE( node );
4635
4636 Exit:
4637 return error;
4638 }

4641 static void
4642 ft_remove_renderer( FT_Module module )
4643 {
4644 FT_Library library;
4645 FT_Memory memory;
4646 FT_ListNode node;
4647
4648
4649 library = module->library;
4650 if ( !library )
4651 return;
4652
4653 memory = library->memory;
4654
4655 node = FT_List_Find( &library->renderers, module );
4656 if ( node )
4657 {
4658 FT_Renderer render = FT_RENDERER( module );
4659
4660
4661 /* release raster object, if any */
4662 if ( render->raster )
4663 render->clazz->raster_class->raster_done( render->raster );
4664
4665 /* remove from list */
4666 FT_List_Remove( &library->renderers, node );
4667 FT_FREE( node );
4668
4669 ft_set_current_renderer( library );
4670 }
4671 }

4688 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
4689 FT_Set_Renderer( FT_Library library,
4690 FT_Renderer renderer,
4691 FT_UInt num_params,
4692 FT_Parameter* parameters )
4693 {
4694 FT_ListNode node;
4695 FT_Error error = FT_Err_Ok;
4696
4697 FT_Renderer_SetModeFunc set_mode;
4698
4699
4700 if ( !library )
4701 {
4702 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Library_Handle );
4703 goto Exit;
4704 }
4705
4706 if ( !renderer )
4707 {
4708 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
4709 goto Exit;
4710 }
4711
4712 if ( num_params > 0 && !parameters )
4713 {
4714 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
4715 goto Exit;
4716 }
4717
4718 node = FT_List_Find( &library->renderers, renderer );
4719 if ( !node )
4720 {
4721 error = FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
4722 goto Exit;
4723 }
4724
4725 FT_List_Up( &library->renderers, node );
4726
4727 if ( renderer->glyph_format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE )
4728 library->cur_renderer = renderer;
4729
4730 set_mode = renderer->clazz->set_mode;
4731
4732 for ( ; num_params > 0; num_params-- )
4733 {
4734 error = set_mode( renderer, parameters->tag, parameters->data );
4735 if ( error )
4736 break;
4737 parameters++;
4738 }
4739
4740 Exit:
4741 return error;

4744
4745 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Error )
4746 FT_Render_Glyph_Internal( FT_Library library,
4747 FT_GlyphSlot slot,
4748 FT_Render_Mode render_mode )
4749 {
4750 FT_Error error = FT_Err_Ok;
4751 FT_Face face = slot->face;
4752 FT_Renderer renderer;
4753
4754
4755 switch ( slot->format )
4756 {
4757 default:
4758 if ( slot->internal->load_flags & FT_LOAD_COLOR )
4759 {
4760 FT_LayerIterator iterator;
4761
4762 FT_UInt base_glyph = slot->glyph_index;
4763
4764 FT_Bool have_layers;
4765 FT_UInt glyph_index;
4766 FT_UInt color_index;
4767
4768
4769 /* check whether we have colored glyph layers */
4770 iterator.p = NULL;
4771 have_layers = FT_Get_Color_Glyph_Layer( face,
4772 base_glyph,
4773 &glyph_index,
4774 &color_index,
4775 &iterator );
4776 if ( have_layers )
4777 {
4778 error = FT_New_GlyphSlot( face, NULL );
4779 if ( !error )
4780 {
4781 TT_Face ttface = (TT_Face)face;
4782 SFNT_Service sfnt = (SFNT_Service)ttface->sfnt;
4783
4784
4785 do
4786 {
4787 FT_Int32 load_flags = slot->internal->load_flags;
4788
4789
4790 /* disable the `FT_LOAD_COLOR' flag to avoid recursion */
4791 /* right here in this function */
4792 load_flags &= ~FT_LOAD_COLOR;
4793
4794 /* render into the new `face->glyph' glyph slot */
4795 load_flags |= FT_LOAD_RENDER;
4796
4797 error = FT_Load_Glyph( face, glyph_index, load_flags );
4798 if ( error )
4799 break;
4800
4801 /* blend new `face->glyph' into old `slot'; */
4802 /* at the first call, `slot' is still empty */
4803 error = sfnt->colr_blend( ttface,
4804 color_index,
4805 slot,
4806 face->glyph );
4807 if ( error )
4808 break;
4809
4810 } while ( FT_Get_Color_Glyph_Layer( face,
4811 base_glyph,
4812 &glyph_index,
4813 &color_index,
4814 &iterator ) );
4815
4816 if ( !error )
4817 slot->format = FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_BITMAP;
4818
4819 /* this call also restores `slot' as the glyph slot */
4820 FT_Done_GlyphSlot( face->glyph );
4821 }
4822
4823 if ( !error )
4824 return error;
4825
4826 /* Failed to do the colored layer. Draw outline instead. */
4827 slot->format = FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE;
4828 }
4829 }
4830
4831 {
4832 FT_ListNode node = NULL;
4833
4834
4835 /* small shortcut for the very common case */
4836 if ( slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE )
4837 {
4838 renderer = library->cur_renderer;
4839 node = library->renderers.head;
4840 }
4841 else
4842 renderer = FT_Lookup_Renderer( library, slot->format, &node );
4843
4844 error = FT_ERR( Cannot_Render_Glyph );
4845 while ( renderer )
4846 {
4847 error = renderer->render( renderer, slot, render_mode, NULL );
4848 if ( !error ||
4849 FT_ERR_NEQ( error, Cannot_Render_Glyph ) )
4850 break;
4851
4852 /* FT_Err_Cannot_Render_Glyph is returned if the render mode */
4853 /* is unsupported by the current renderer for this glyph image */
4854 /* format. */
4855
4856 /* now, look for another renderer that supports the same */
4857 /* format. */
4858 renderer = FT_Lookup_Renderer( library, slot->format, &node );
4859 }
4860
4861 /* it is not an error if we cannot render a bitmap glyph */
4862 if ( FT_ERR_EQ( error, Cannot_Render_Glyph ) &&
4863 slot->format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_BITMAP )
4864 error = FT_Err_Ok;
4865 }
4866 }
4867
4868#ifdef FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_TRACE
4869
4870#undef FT_COMPONENT
4871#define FT_COMPONENT checksum
4872
4873 /*
4874 * Computing the MD5 checksum is expensive, unnecessarily distorting a
4875 * possible profiling of FreeType if compiled with tracing support. For
4876 * this reason, we execute the following code only if explicitly
4877 * requested.
4878 */
4879
4880 /* we use FT_TRACE3 in this block */
4881 if ( !error &&
4882 ft_trace_levels[trace_checksum] >= 3 &&
4883 slot->bitmap.buffer )
4884 {
4885 FT_Bitmap bitmap;
4886 FT_Error err;
4887
4888
4889 FT_Bitmap_Init( &bitmap );
4890
4891 /* we convert to a single bitmap format for computing the checksum */
4892 /* this also converts the bitmap flow to `down' (i.e., pitch > 0) */
4893 err = FT_Bitmap_Convert( library, &slot->bitmap, &bitmap, 1 );
4894 if ( !err )
4895 {
4896 MD5_CTX ctx;
4897 unsigned char md5[16];
4898 unsigned long coverage = 0;
4899 int i, j;
4900 int rows = (int)bitmap.rows;
4901 int pitch = bitmap.pitch;
4902
4903
4904 FT_TRACE3(( "FT_Render_Glyph: bitmap %dx%d, %s (mode %d)\n",
4905 pitch,
4906 rows,
4907 pixel_modes[slot->bitmap.pixel_mode],
4908 slot->bitmap.pixel_mode ));
4909
4910 for ( i = 0; i < rows; i++ )
4911 for ( j = 0; j < pitch; j++ )
4912 coverage += bitmap.buffer[i * pitch + j];
4913
4914 FT_TRACE3(( " Total coverage: %lu\n", coverage ));
4915
4916 MD5_Init( &ctx );
4917 if ( bitmap.buffer )
4918 MD5_Update( &ctx, bitmap.buffer,
4919 (unsigned long)rows * (unsigned long)pitch );
4920 MD5_Final( md5, &ctx );
4921
4922 FT_TRACE3(( " MD5 checksum: " ));
4923 for ( i = 0; i < 16; i++ )
4924 FT_TRACE3(( "%02X", md5[i] ));
4925 FT_TRACE3(( "\n" ));
4926 }
4927
4928 FT_Bitmap_Done( library, &bitmap );
4929 }
4930
4931 /*
4932 * Dump bitmap in Netpbm format (PBM or PGM).
4933 */
4934
4935 /* we use FT_TRACE7 in this block */
4936 if ( !error &&
4937 ft_trace_levels[trace_checksum] >= 7 &&
4938 slot->bitmap.buffer )
4939 {
4940 if ( slot->bitmap.rows < 128U &&
4941 slot->bitmap.width < 128U )
4942 {
4943 int rows = (int)slot->bitmap.rows;
4944 int width = (int)slot->bitmap.width;
4945 int pitch = slot->bitmap.pitch;
4946 int i, j, m;
4947
4948 unsigned char* topleft = slot->bitmap.buffer;
4949
4950
4951 if ( pitch < 0 )
4952 topleft -= pitch * ( rows - 1 );
4953
4954 FT_TRACE7(( "Netpbm image: start\n" ));
4955 switch ( slot->bitmap.pixel_mode )
4956 {
4957 case FT_PIXEL_MODE_MONO:
4958 FT_TRACE7(( "P1 %d %d\n", width, rows ));
4959 for ( i = 0; i < rows; i++ )
4960 {
4961 for ( j = 0; j < width; )
4962 for ( m = 128; m > 0 && j < width; m >>= 1, j++ )
4963 FT_TRACE7(( " %d",
4964 ( topleft[i * pitch + j / 8] & m ) != 0 ));
4965 FT_TRACE7(( "\n" ));
4966 }
4967 break;
4968
4969 default:
4970 FT_TRACE7(( "P2 %d %d 255\n", width, rows ));
4971 for ( i = 0; i < rows; i++ )
4972 {
4973 for ( j = 0; j < width; j += 1 )
4974 FT_TRACE7(( " %3u", topleft[i * pitch + j] ));
4975 FT_TRACE7(( "\n" ));
4976 }
4977 }
4978 FT_TRACE7(( "Netpbm image: end\n" ));
4979 }
4980 else
4981 FT_TRACE7(( "Netpbm image: too large, omitted\n" ));
4982 }
4983
4984#undef FT_COMPONENT
4985#define FT_COMPONENT objs
4986
4987#endif /* FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_TRACE */
4988
4989 return error;
4990 }

5024 /**************************************************************************
5025 *
5026 * @Function:
5027 * Destroy_Module
5028 *
5029 * @Description:
5030 * Destroys a given module object. For drivers, this also destroys
5031 * all child faces.
5032 *
5033 * @InOut:
5034 * module ::
5035 * A handle to the target driver object.
5036 *
5037 * @Note:
5038 * The driver _must_ be LOCKED!
5039 */
5040 static void
5041 Destroy_Module( FT_Module module )
5042 {
5043 FT_Memory memory = module->memory;
5044 FT_Module_Class* clazz = module->clazz;
5045 FT_Library library = module->library;
5046
5047
5048 if ( library && library->auto_hinter == module )
5049 library->auto_hinter = NULL;
5050
5051 /* if the module is a renderer */
5052 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_RENDERER( module ) )
5053 ft_remove_renderer( module );
5054
5055 /* if the module is a font driver, add some steps */
5056 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_DRIVER( module ) )
5057 Destroy_Driver( FT_DRIVER( module ) );
5058
5059 /* finalize the module object */
5060 if ( clazz->module_done )
5061 clazz->module_done( module );
5062
5063 /* discard it */
5064 FT_FREE( module );
5065 }

5068 /* documentation is in ftmodapi.h */
5069
5070 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
5071 FT_Add_Module( FT_Library library,
5072 const FT_Module_Class* clazz )
5073 {
5074 FT_Error error;
5075 FT_Memory memory;
5076 FT_Module module = NULL;
5077 FT_UInt nn;
5078
5079
5080#define FREETYPE_VER_FIXED ( ( (FT_Long)FREETYPE_MAJOR << 16 ) | \
5081 FREETYPE_MINOR )
5082
5083 if ( !library )
5084 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Library_Handle );
5085
5086 if ( !clazz )
5087 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
5088
5089 /* check FreeType version */
5090 if ( clazz->module_requires > FREETYPE_VER_FIXED )
5091 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Version );
5092
5093 /* look for a module with the same name in the library's table */
5094 for ( nn = 0; nn < library->num_modules; nn++ )
5095 {
5096 module = library->modules[nn];
5097 if ( ft_strcmp( module->clazz->module_name, clazz->module_name ) == 0 )
5098 {
5099 /* this installed module has the same name, compare their versions */
5100 if ( clazz->module_version <= module->clazz->module_version )
5101 return FT_THROW( Lower_Module_Version );
5102
5103 /* remove the module from our list, then exit the loop to replace */
5104 /* it by our new version.. */
5105 FT_Remove_Module( library, module );
5106 break;
5107 }
5108 }
5109
5110 memory = library->memory;
5111 error = FT_Err_Ok;
5112
5113 if ( library->num_modules >= FT_MAX_MODULES )
5114 {
5115 error = FT_THROW( Too_Many_Drivers );
5116 goto Exit;
5117 }
5118
5119 /* allocate module object */
5120 if ( FT_ALLOC( module, clazz->module_size ) )
5121 goto Exit;
5122
5123 /* base initialization */
5124 module->library = library;
5125 module->memory = memory;
5126 module->clazz = (FT_Module_Class*)clazz;
5127
5128 /* check whether the module is a renderer - this must be performed */
5129 /* before the normal module initialization */
5130 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_RENDERER( module ) )
5131 {
5132 /* add to the renderers list */
5133 error = ft_add_renderer( module );
5134 if ( error )
5135 goto Fail;
5136 }
5137
5138 /* is the module a auto-hinter? */
5139 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_HINTER( module ) )
5140 library->auto_hinter = module;
5141
5142 /* if the module is a font driver */
5143 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_DRIVER( module ) )
5144 {
5145 FT_Driver driver = FT_DRIVER( module );
5146
5147
5148 driver->clazz = (FT_Driver_Class)module->clazz;
5149 }
5150
5151 if ( clazz->module_init )
5152 {
5153 error = clazz->module_init( module );
5154 if ( error )
5155 goto Fail;
5156 }
5157
5158 /* add module to the library's table */
5159 library->modules[library->num_modules++] = module;
5160
5161 Exit:
5162 return error;
5163
5164 Fail:
5165 if ( FT_MODULE_IS_RENDERER( module ) )
5166 {
5167 FT_Renderer renderer = FT_RENDERER( module );
5168
5169
5170 if ( renderer->clazz &&
5171 renderer->clazz->glyph_format == FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_OUTLINE &&
5172 renderer->raster )
5173 renderer->clazz->raster_class->raster_done( renderer->raster );
5174 }
5175
5176 FT_FREE( module );
5177 goto Exit;
5178 }

5226 FT_BASE_DEF( FT_Pointer )
5227 ft_module_get_service( FT_Module module,
5228 const char* service_id,
5229 FT_Bool global )
5230 {
5231 FT_Pointer result = NULL;
5232
5233
5234 if ( module )
5235 {
5236 FT_ASSERT( module->clazz && module->clazz->get_interface );
5237
5238 /* first, look for the service in the module */
5239 if ( module->clazz->get_interface )
5240 result = module->clazz->get_interface( module, service_id );
5241
5242 if ( global && !result )
5243 {
5244 /* we didn't find it, look in all other modules then */
5245 FT_Library library = module->library;
5246 FT_Module* cur = library->modules;
5247 FT_Module* limit = cur + library->num_modules;
5248
5249
5250 for ( ; cur < limit; cur++ )
5251 {
5252 if ( cur[0] != module )
5253 {
5254 FT_ASSERT( cur[0]->clazz );
5255
5256 if ( cur[0]->clazz->get_interface )
5257 {
5258 result = cur[0]->clazz->get_interface( cur[0], service_id );
5259 if ( result )
5260 break;
5261 }
5262 }
5263 }
5264 }
5265 }
5266
5267 return result;
5268 }

5272
5273 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
5274 FT_Remove_Module( FT_Library library,
5275 FT_Module module )
5276 {
5277 /* try to find the module from the table, then remove it from there */
5278
5279 if ( !library )
5280 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Library_Handle );
5281
5282 if ( module )
5283 {
5284 FT_Module* cur = library->modules;
5285 FT_Module* limit = cur + library->num_modules;
5286
5287
5288 for ( ; cur < limit; cur++ )
5289 {
5290 if ( cur[0] == module )
5291 {
5292 /* remove it from the table */
5293 library->num_modules--;
5294 limit--;
5295 while ( cur < limit )
5296 {
5297 cur[0] = cur[1];
5298 cur++;
5299 }
5300 limit[0] = NULL;
5301
5302 /* destroy the module */
5303 Destroy_Module( module );
5304
5305 return FT_Err_Ok;
5306 }
5307 }
5308 }
5309 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Driver_Handle );
5310 }

5313 static FT_Error
5314 ft_property_do( FT_Library library,
5315 const FT_String* module_name,
5316 const FT_String* property_name,
5317 void* value,
5318 FT_Bool set,
5319 FT_Bool value_is_string )
5320 {
5321 FT_Module* cur;
5322 FT_Module* limit;
5323 FT_Module_Interface interface;
5324
5325 FT_Service_Properties service;
5326
5327#ifdef FT_DEBUG_LEVEL_ERROR
5328 const FT_String* set_name = "FT_Property_Set";
5329 const FT_String* get_name = "FT_Property_Get";
5330 const FT_String* func_name = set ? set_name : get_name;
5331#endif
5332
5333 FT_Bool missing_func;
5334
5335
5336 if ( !library )
5337 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Library_Handle );
5338
5339 if ( !module_name || !property_name || !value )
5340 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Argument );
5341
5342 cur = library->modules;
5343 limit = cur + library->num_modules;
5344
5345 /* search module */
5346 for ( ; cur < limit; cur++ )
5347 if ( !ft_strcmp( cur[0]->clazz->module_name, module_name ) )
5348 break;
5349
5350 if ( cur == limit )
5351 {
5352 FT_TRACE2(( "%s: can't find module `%s'\n",
5353 func_name, module_name ));
5354 return FT_THROW( Missing_Module );
5355 }
5356
5357 /* check whether we have a service interface */
5358 if ( !cur[0]->clazz->get_interface )
5359 {
5360 FT_TRACE2(( "%s: module `%s' doesn't support properties\n",
5361 func_name, module_name ));
5362 return FT_THROW( Unimplemented_Feature );
5363 }
5364
5365 /* search property service */
5366 interface = cur[0]->clazz->get_interface( cur[0],
5367 FT_SERVICE_ID_PROPERTIES );
5368 if ( !interface )
5369 {
5370 FT_TRACE2(( "%s: module `%s' doesn't support properties\n",
5371 func_name, module_name ));
5372 return FT_THROW( Unimplemented_Feature );
5373 }
5374
5375 service = (FT_Service_Properties)interface;
5376
5377 if ( set )
5378 missing_func = FT_BOOL( !service->set_property );
5379 else
5380 missing_func = FT_BOOL( !service->get_property );
5381
5382 if ( missing_func )
5383 {
5384 FT_TRACE2(( "%s: property service of module `%s' is broken\n",
5385 func_name, module_name ));
5386 return FT_THROW( Unimplemented_Feature );
5387 }
5388
5389 return set ? service->set_property( cur[0],
5390 property_name,
5391 value,
5392 value_is_string )
5393 : service->get_property( cur[0],
5394 property_name,
5395 value );
5396 }

5490

5553
5554 FT_EXPORT_DEF( FT_Error )
5555 FT_Done_Library( FT_Library library )
5556 {
5557 FT_Memory memory;
5558
5559
5560 if ( !library )
5561 return FT_THROW( Invalid_Library_Handle );
5562
5563 library->refcount--;
5564 if ( library->refcount > 0 )
5565 goto Exit;
5566
5567 memory = library->memory;
5568
5569 /*
5570 * Close all faces in the library. If we don't do this, we can have
5571 * some subtle memory leaks.
5572 *
5573 * Example:
5574 *
5575 * - the cff font driver uses the pshinter module in cff_size_done
5576 * - if the pshinter module is destroyed before the cff font driver,
5577 * opened FT_Face objects managed by the driver are not properly
5578 * destroyed, resulting in a memory leak
5579 *
5580 * Some faces are dependent on other faces, like Type42 faces that
5581 * depend on TrueType faces synthesized internally.
5582 *
5583 * The order of drivers should be specified in driver_name[].
5584 */
5585 {
5586 FT_UInt m, n;
5587 const char* driver_name[] = { "type42", NULL };
5588
5589
5590 for ( m = 0;
5591 m < sizeof ( driver_name ) / sizeof ( driver_name[0] );
5592 m++ )
5593 {
5594 for ( n = 0; n < library->num_modules; n++ )
5595 {
5596 FT_Module module = library->modules[n];
5597 const char* module_name = module->clazz->module_name;
5598 FT_List faces;
5599
5600
5601 if ( driver_name[m] &&
5602 ft_strcmp( module_name, driver_name[m] ) != 0 )
5603 continue;
5604
5605 if ( ( module->clazz->module_flags & FT_MODULE_FONT_DRIVER ) == 0 )
5606 continue;
5607
5608 FT_TRACE7(( "FT_Done_Library: close faces for %s\n", module_name ));
5609
5610 faces = &FT_DRIVER( module )->faces_list;
5611 while ( faces->head )
5612 {
5613 FT_Done_Face( FT_FACE( faces->head->data ) );
5614 if ( faces->head )
5615 FT_TRACE0(( "FT_Done_Library: failed to free some faces\n" ));
5616 }
5617 }
5618 }
5619 }
5620
5621 /* Close all other modules in the library */
5622#if 1
5623 /* XXX Modules are removed in the reversed order so that */
5624 /* type42 module is removed before truetype module. This */
5625 /* avoids double free in some occasions. It is a hack. */
5626 while ( library->num_modules > 0 )
5627 FT_Remove_Module( library,
5628 library->modules[library->num_modules - 1] );
5629#else
5630 {
5631 FT_UInt n;
5632
5633
5634 for ( n = 0; n < library->num_modules; n++ )
5635 {
5636 FT_Module module = library->modules[n];
5637
5638
5639 if ( module )
5640 {
5641 Destroy_Module( module );
5642 library->modules[n] = NULL;
5643 }
5644 }
5645 }
5646#endif
5647
5648 FT_FREE( library );
5649
5650 Exit:
5651 return FT_Err_Ok;
5652 }
